Commentary: A bit of a wayward start from Bumrah. A good length ball but it is way outside off. Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Gets closer this time and bowls this ball in the channel outside off. Burns lets it go to the keeper again.
Beats the outside edge this time! Perfect line and length and seems like Bumrah has found his rhythm. A length delivery just outside off, Burns pokes at it but makes no connection.
Bat on ball for the first time. This is fullish and just outside off, Burns comes on the front foot and pushes it towards the cover region.
In the channel outside off, Burns offers no shot.

Beaten! Good testing first over from Bumrah! After bowling good length deliveries, Bumrah bowls it full and wide outside off, asking Burns to go for the drive and Burns obliges but without any stride. Lucky not to edge it behind. A maiden to begin from Bumrah.
Yadav runs in and bowls the length ball outside off, Wade covers his stumps and lets it be.
Full and wide outside off, Wade is not lured into going for the drive way from his body as he shoulders arms.
Another one outside off, Wade is happy leaving it alone this early in his innings.
Outside off, easy leave again.

Wade and Australia are underway! Full and wide outside off, Wade this time goes for the drive and finds the gap at cover-point. The cover fielder gives it a chase and returns the ball to the keeper but not before the Aussie openers take three.
Little too wide for the right-hander. Burns lets it go to the keeper. The ball moves late in the air.
Good length and around off, Wade covers his stumps and lets it go.
Fuller and around off, Wade keeps it out.
Nicely bowled! A length ball around middle and off, Wade looks to defend but it comes back in a touch. He misses to get hit high on the pad.
Outside off, left alone.
Misfield and a run! First run off Bumrah. A length ball around off, Wade pushes it towards the left of Gully. Rahane there misfields and allows a single.

That's an absolute ripper! What a delivery to end the over. A fuller ball just outside off, Burns comes forward and looks to defned as he plays for the swing but it goes straight to beat the outside edge. Another fine over from Bumrah.
Fine shot for nothing. Full and wide outside off, Wade nails the drive but finds Jadeja at covers.

Is that a drop? Has Wade got a life here? A lovely ball from Umesh. A length ball around off, Wade is squared up as he looks to defend. The ball goes to the left of debutant Gill at second slip. He dives to that side but it looked like it bounced just before his hands. They take two as the ball goes towards third man. A chance but it was a very difficult one.
FOUR! Gorgeous drive! Full and wide outside off, Wade this time drills it through cover-point and it races away to the fence.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
Around off on a length, Wade defends it out.
Length ball around off and middle, Wade keeps it out solidly.
Good length and around off, pushed to the left of the bowler.

OUT! TAKEN! Bumrah draws first blood. Lovely stuff from him. Burns poor run continues as he departs for a duck. Bumrah runs in and bowls a good length ball just outside off, Burns comes on the front foot and looks to defend but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes behind and it is a simple chance for Pant. They all go up in appeal and the finger is raised.
Good length and just outside off, blocked.

What a ripper! Bumrah is looking superb for the Indians here. Another brilliant delivery from him. It is just outside off on a good length. Maybe a little on the shortish side. Marnus stays back and has a poke off his back foot but is beaten.
Little wide outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.
Fullish and on middle, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid on. End of a successful over for Bumrah.
FOUR! SHOT! Superb shot! Umesh is looking for some swing and hence he is pitching it up. This one is wide outside off and Wade creams it through the cover region for a boundary.
Taps the next one towards point and gets to the other end. Good stuff from Wade.
Labuschagne is up and running now! Umesh sprays on the pads and he flicks it to fine leg for one.
Full but wide outside off, left alone by Wade.
Down the leg side. Wade lets it be.
On the pads again, Wade nudges it through square leg for a single to keep the strike for the next over.
Good leave! This was just outside off and it came back in nicely as Wade allowed it to go to the keeper. Top stuff from Bumrah here.
This one comes back again as Wade is hit high on the pad.
Nicely done! Full ball on middle, Wade flicks it through mid-wicket and runs three before Ashwin can return the ball.
Good length and around off, kept out.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Labuschagne makes another leave as Bumrah bowls it outside off on a good length.
Fuller but wide outside off, Wade lets it go to Pant.
Another fuller one outside off, Wade is not interested again.
Beaten this time! Umesh runs in and bowls it just outside off, Wade this time goes for the big booming drive but a hint of away movement means he makes no connection.
A length ball this time and it is outside off. A leave this time from Wade.
Excellent stuff from Umesh in this over. Pitches this one around off and middle and it is shortish in length. It comes back in as Wade looks to defend. He misses to get hit high on the pad.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Fuller and outside off, driven well but straight to the cover fielder.
Around off on a good length, blocked.
Another good length delivery around off, blocked off the back foot.
Goes for the bouncer but this one doesn't rise much. Labuschagne pulls it wide of the fine leg fielder for a brace.
Wide outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Good fuller length ball outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Fuller length outside off, Wade drives this one through covers to collect three more runs.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
Close to the off stump on a length, but still left alone by Marnus.
Good ball to end the over. A length ball around off, jags back in to hit Marnus on the pads.
Flatter and around off to begin, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller and around off and middle, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter and outside off, tucked towards square leg.
Just wide! Good stuff from Ashwin. Flat and around off, turns in and bounces extra. It lobs wide of the leg slip. Replays show there was some bat. Labuschagne is a lucky man.
Quicker one just outside off, Labuschagne goes on the back foot and looks to cut but misses.
Dot to end! Good first over from Ashwin. Fuller and around middle, Labuschagne flicks but the short leg fielder stops.
Driven nicely! Full and wide, Wade drives it to the right side of the man at mid off. The fielder gives it a chase but Wade gets three more.
Outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.
A fuller length ball on middle, flicked to mid on.
Another one that jags back in. A length ball outside off, comes back sharply to hit Marnus on the pads. He thought this one will move away but it came back in but hit him high on the pad.
A length ball outside off, defended straight back.
Fuller ball on the pads, flicked away towards fine leg for a single.
Shortish and just outsude off, punched towards cover for a single.
Full and outside off, Wade goes for the sweep but misses. It bounces extra as Pant fails to catch it as it hits him near his chest.
Floated around off, blocked off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely done! Full and on middle and leg, Wade gets in position and nicely paddles it through short fine leg for a boundary. Wade moves to 30 off just 38 balls.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja holds on! There was some confusion but he did really well to keep his eyes on the ball to hold onto it. A poor shot from Wade. He was playing aggressively and he once again tried to go after Ashwin. A Tossed up ball around off and middle, Wade dances down the track and looks to hammer it on the leg side but ends up getting a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards mid-wicket. Jadeja and Gill go for the catch but Jadeja calls for it but Gill doesn't see that. They both go for it and almost collides with each other. However, Jadeja keeps his eyes on the ball to take a fine catch.
A mild appeal! A tossed up ball around the pad, Labuschagne lets it be and is hit on the pad. An enquiry but turned down. End of a successful over from Ashwin.
Fuller length ball on the stumps, defended straight back.
Good length ball outside off, Smith shuffles and plays it towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, Smith bunts this out.
A fuller length ball outside off, Smith plays it towards mid on.
A length ball just outside off, left alone by Smith.
Maiden over first up to Smith. A length ball outside off, blocked by Smith towards mid on.
Quick single! Flatter and around middle, Labuschagne goes back and pushes it towards mid off. They go for a single.

Turn and bounce! Tossed up around middle, it pitches and then boucnes an turns sharply as Smith is beaten. Pant fails to collecy to his left as well and they run two byes as the ball goes towards fine leg.

OUT! TAKEN DOWN THE LEG SIDE! Ashwin removes the big fish. Smith falls for a duck. Lovely from Ashwin. Bowls a loopy ball around middle and leg, Smith lunges forward to work it on the leg side but ends up hitting it straight to the leg slip fielder. Pujara there takes a good catch. Ashwin removes Smith again. Terrific stuff from the Indians here.
Full and around off, driven towards mid off.
On off, kept out.
Flatter and around middle, Head goes back to block it out.
Length ball outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! It is going over the stumps. Extra bounce saves Head. A length ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend but this one comes back in nicely and beats the inside edge. The ball hits the pad and the Indians appeal but nothing from the umpire. Indians take it upstairs. Replays roll in and they show that the ball would go over the timbers. India lose their review.
Length ball outside off, nudged it soflty towards mid on and Marnus takes a quick single.
Fuller ball on the stumps, Head flick this one to mid on
A length ball outside off, Head blocks this one out.
Beaten! Superb delivery from Bumrah. Just around off on a good length. Head has to play at it. He does so but is beaten all ends up. Terrific from Bumrah.
Flatter and just around off, punched towards cover.
Flatter and just outside off, forced to deep cover for a run.
On the pads, worked towards the square leg fielder. It went uppishly but was wide of the man at short leg.
On off, kept out.
Full and on middle, forced towards mid on.
Dot to end! Flatter and around off, Head goes back and pushes it towards cover.
Length ball just outside off, Marnus defends it solidly.
A fuller length ball, Marnus watches and plays it towards point.
Length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
A good length ball around off, defended solidly on the front foot by Marnus.
A fuller ball on the stumps, Marnus misses and gets hit on the pads. Inside edge there seem to save him from getting trapped right in front.
A length ball outside off, defended on the leg side.
Loopy ball outside off, Head drives it hard but it hits Vihari at silly point.

What happened there? Floated around off, Head looks to work it on the leg side but it spins away to beat the bat. The ball hits his pad and then lobs towards silly point. The fielder takes the catch and they appeal but not out says the umpire. The Indians think for the review but in the end opt against it.
Flatter and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
On off, this time Head comes forward and keeps it out.
Fuller and around middle, blocked.
Single to end another superb over from Ashwin. Full and wide, Head goes for the drive and connects it well. It is to the right side of Jadeja who makes a diving stop but they take the single.
Fuller and around off to begin, pushed off the front foot towards point.
Full again, pushed towards mid off.
Flatter and just outside off, punched towards the off side.
Floats this one down the leg side. Head looks to flick but misses.
On middle, pushed to mid on for a quick single.
Flatter and around off, worked wide of the man at mid on for a run. Decent start from Jadeja.
Play and a miss! A flatter ball just outside off, Labuschagne looks to punch it off the back foot but it bounces extra and Labuschagne fails to connect.
Flatter and around middle, blocked.
Short and just outside off, Labuschagne punches but finds the cover fielder.
FOUR! Crunched! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne rocks back and slams it wide of Jadeja this time. He gives it a chase but fails to stop.
Fuller and around off, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Around off and middle, Head stays back to keep it out.
Full and wide, driven hard but straight to Gill at short cover.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and around off, Labuschagne does well to block off his back foot.
Beaten this time! Jadeja fires this one just outside off, it pitches and then turns away a touch. Good take from Pant.
This time Labuschagne gets behind the line to defend off his front foot.
A maiden from Jadeja. Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.
Floated on middle, played back to Ashwin by Head.
Tossed up on middle, Head stays back and blocks.
Down the leg side, flicked wide of the man at square leg for a run.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single. The single brings up 50 for Australia.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to Ashwin.
Floated around middle, Head defends it out.
Short and wide outside off, pushed towards point.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne stays back and then just forces it gently wide of the short third man fielder. It races away to the fence.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks but can't beat the man at mid-wicket who makes a diving stop to his right.
Flatter and around off, blocked.
Fuller and around off, Labuschagne comes forward and defends. Pant encourages Jadeja from behind, telling him to keep bowling the same length.
On middle, defended.
Floated on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked.
Quicker one outside off, Head lets it be.
Flatter and around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
On off, a solid front foot block from Head this time.
Maiden from Ashwin. Flatter and around off, Head keeps it out.
FOUR! Jadeja giving away easy runs here. Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne slams it through point and bags another boundary.
In the air... safe! Jadeja bowls this one full and bowls it wide. Labuschagne reaches out and looks to drive but gets a top edge. The ball lands safely outside the ring at cover. Two taken.
Flat and around off, blocked out.
Tossed up and outside off, driven towards cover for a quick single.
Down the leg side, turns further down as Pant fails to collect it down the leg side. The ball races to the fine leg fence but Mayank does well to get to the ball and pull it back in.
Tossed up and just outside off, turns away a touch as Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper.
Flatter and around off, worked towards the leg side.
Full and on middle, pushed to the left of Ashwin for nothing.
Shortish and around middle, worked towards mid on for a single.

NOT OUT! It is missing the stumps. It never looked that it would be going over the timbers but that is the case and Labuschagne survives. Good use of the technology from him. A tossed up delivery around middle, he goes for the sweep but he misses to get hit on the pad. The Indians appeal and the finger goes up. Marnus calls for the review straightaway. Replays roll now. Hot Spot and RTS show no bat. But to everyone's surprise, the ball is going over the stumps. The extra bounce which Ashwin is generating takes it over the stumps. Good call to review from Labuschagne.
Floated on middle, blocked off the front foot.
Quicker one on the pads, flicked towards the leg side. With that, it is Lunch on Day 1.
Siraj is right on the money! A length delivery around off, Head blocks off his back foot.
Shortish and around off, Head keeps it out.
Back of a length and just outside off, poked towards the point fielder.
In the channel outside off, Head lets it be.
Good length and around off, Head dabs it towards cover and they take a quick run.
On the pads, clipped to fine leg for one. 2 off Siraj's first over in Tests.
Flatter and around middle, worked towards short leg.
Flatter and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Floated on off, blocked off the front foot.
Full and on middle, worked towards square leg. They think for the run but opt against it.
On middle, blocked by Labuschagne.
Just wide! A maiden to begin from Ashwin. Flatter and around middle, bounces extra as Labuschagne fends it wide of the man at short leg.
A length ball on middle, defended straight back.
A fuller length ball across the left hander, Head leaves it alone.
Length ball on middle, pushed towards point.
Short of a length outside off, Head punches it through the covers for a couple.
Length ball on middle, defended straight back to the bowler.
Bouncer to end the over from Siraj. A short bumper on middle and leg, Head ducks under it.
Floated around middle, played towards the cover region.
Fuller ball on middle, defended straight back.
A short ball on the stumps, punched through covers for a single.
Floated around middle, defended straight back.
Floated ball on middle, tucked away towards square leg for a single.
A shortish ball on the stumps, punched towards point for another run.
Short of a length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Length ball on the pads, clipped away towards fine leg for single.
Short of a length, punched straight to mid off.
Short of a length outside off, Head looks to guide it towards third man but Rahane at gully stops it by diving to his left.
Length ball just outside off, punched to the covers for a single.
A length ball outside off, Marnus defends it on the on side.
FOUR BYES! Ashwin bowls it down the leg side, Head looks to flick but misses it. It goes past the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on middle, Head blocks it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on off, Head pushes it to mid off.
Turn and bounce again but down the leg side again. Pant fails to collect again. The ball goes to fine leg for a bye.
Tossed up and around off, blocked.
Floated on middle, kept out.
Nice shot! Full and on the pads, Head flicks it through mid-wicket. Three taken before the ball is returned to the keeper.
This time a length ball on the pads of Marnus. He tucks it through square leg. Fine leg runs to his left and gets to the ball but not before they get a brace.
Length ball around off, watchfully defended.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave.
Another one outside off. It is short as well. Labuschagne makes another leave.

FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Full ball outside off, Labuschagne creams it through the covers. It is going towards the longest part of the ground as the fielder gives it a chase. The fielder is slow in getting down to stop and at the end he needs to stop but getting down first and then pick the ball to throw it back. That allows the batters to run four. It brings 50-run stand between the two.
No run, Length ball around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on middle, clipped through square leg for a couple.
Around off on a length, blocked off the front foot.
Good bumper but Head does well to sway away.
Length ball around off, pushed towards cover.
Back of a length and around off, blocked off the back foot.
Fuller and around off, Labuschagne blocks off his front foot.

Ouch! Is there any bat? Or that came off the helmet. A nasty bumper from Siraj. Labuschagne looked to pull but he gets beaten by the pace and gets a blow on his helmet. The ball lobs towards the slip cordon and Gill goes back to catch. The Indians appeal but nothing from the umpire. No review from the Indians. Replays show it came off the helmet. The good thing is that Labuschagne is looking fine.
Yes, he does! Another well-directed bumper! This time Labuschagne gets out of the way.
Fuller and around off, tucked wide of the man at mid-wicket for one.
Good length and around off, kept out.
A single! Shortish and around middle, clipped through square leg for a run by Head.
A bumper now to Head. A short ball on middle, Head ducks under it.

EDGY FOUR! Full and wide outside off, Head throws his bat at it but gets a thick outside edge which goes past the diving backward point fielder. Rahane and Siraj then gives it a chase but the ball wins the race to the fence.
A Short of a length ball around off, Head blocks this out.
Shortish around off, Head shuffles and tucks this towards fine leg for a single.
Another short ball but outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
A length ball on off, defended watchfully on the off side.
Length ball around off, defended straight back.
FOUR! Driven superbly to bring up 100 for the Aussies. A low full toss, Head creams it through the cover region for a boundary.
Short of a length ball outside off, Head blocks this on the off side.
A length ball outside off, driven straight to mid off.
A length ball just outside off, Head punches this one through the covers to collect a couple of runs more.
Another single. A Shortish ball around off, Head cuts this one towards point for a run.
Length ball around off, blocked on the off side.
A length ball on pads, tucked through square leg for a single.
One more single! Fuller and around off, worked towards square leg for a run.
A bumper on middle. Head sits under it.
Back of a length and on middle and leg, Head works it towards mid-wicket and takes one.
Length ball around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball around off, pushed towards mid off.
Sharp bumper! It is just outside off, Head does well to back away.
Shortish and on middle, tucked through mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball on middle and leg, pulled to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! FLICKED! Bumrah bowls a full toss on the pads, a freebie for Head and he accepts it by flicking it through square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Glorious drive! Has to be shot off the day. A full ball outside off, Head creams it through mid off for another boundary.
Full and on the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket for nothing.

EDGY FOUR! Runs coming thick and fast for Australia. A full ball just outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge that goes past the slip fielder and into the third man fence.
Around off on a length, kept out.
A bouncer arond off, Labuschagne sits under it.
NO BALL! A length ball around off, Labuschagne blocks it out. Yadav has overstepped which is confirmed by the TV umpire.
Length ball around middle, tucked towards square leg. They think for a single but decide against it.
Back of a length and on middle and leg, clipped towards square leg for nothing.
Fuller and around off, Head pushes it towards the cover fielder.
NO BALL! Shortish around off, pushed on the off side. Bumrah oversteps this time.
Short bumper around middle, Head ducks under it.
Short again on the body, Head tucks this on the on side.
Short ball around the ribs, Head tries to play but the ball bounces over him.
No BALL! Length ball around middle, clipped straight to mid wicket.

OUT! TAKEN! Bumrah gets the breakthrough. How many times has he done that for his team? Almost every time. A good length ball just around off, it comes back in as Head has a poke at it. He ends up getting a thick outside edge which goes to the right side of gully. It goes quickly but the Indian skipper is alert as he does really well to move to his right and take the catch nicely. A fine knock from Head comes to an end.
Fuller and around off, Green keeps it out. End of a successful over from Bumrah.
A good length ball around off, defended straight back.
Beautiful Delivery this! A good length ball outside off, shapes away after pitching and Marnus is beaten on that one.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Length ball down the leg side, Marnus misses his flick and it is through to the keeper.
Fuller ball on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball outside off, defended solidly by Green.
Length ball around off, defended on the on side.
Fuller this time around off, played to the covers.
Fuller ball around off stump, Marnus defends it watchfully.
A good length ball outside off, left alone.
Short of a length around middle, pulled away towards fine leg for a single.
WIDE! A bouncer to the new batsman Green. But it is way too high reckons the Umpire and thereby wided.
A length ball around off, Green plays it on the off side.
Length ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.
A length ball around off, Marnus defends it on the off side.
Shortish ball around middle, tucked away on the leg side.
Short of a length around off, defended solidly.
A good length ball on the stumps, Marnus plays it towards mid off.

A length ball around middle and leg, jags back in and hits Marnus on the pads, who misses his flick. A bit of appeal from the bowler and the keeper but Rahane is not too convinced for the review. Replays show the ball missing leg stump. Wise decision from India not to waste a review.
Good work down the leg side from Pant. Bumrah sprays it down the leg side. Green looks to flick but misses. Pant does well to get to the ball on his left with a tumble.
Green is off the mark with a fine stroke. Full ball around off, he comes on the front foot and drives it through covers. Three taken.
Shortish and around off, kept out off the front foot.
Good bumper! Labuschagne does well to get away from the line of the delivery.
Around off on a length, kept out off the front foot.
End of another probing over from Bumrah. Around off on a good length, Labuschagne looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the pad.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
Tossed up and just outside off, Green comes down the track and defends.
Floated around off, blocked.
Very full down the leg side. Green looks to flick but misses.
Shortish and around off, punched wide of the point fielder for a run.
On middle, driven towards the cover fielder.
A fuller ball around off, Green drives it nicely but straight to mid on.
Good length ball on the stumps, defended towards mid on.
A length ball outside off, comes back in sharply but left alone by Green on the length.
Fullish delivery on the stumps, driven to mid on.
A bouncer on middle, Green ducks under it.
Shortish length ball defended straight back.
Floated on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and around middle and leg, worked towards square leg.
Tossed up and outside off, Labuschagne drills it through the covers. Yadav gives it a chase and keeps it down to 3.
On off, blocked.
Shortish and on middle, turned on the leg side for nothing.
Tossed up and on middle, tucked to the man at mid-wicket.
Fullish ball on the stumps, defended straight towards mid on.
Length ball around off, poked towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj strikes! His first Test wicket and it is the other debutant, Gill who takes a fine catch. A huge wicket for India. Perfect field placement from Rahane and Siraj delivers the delivery. Full and on the pads, Labuschagne is just 2 short of a half ton. He gets the ball on his pads and looks to flick. He fails to keep it down as it goes to the right side of the backward square leg fielder. Gill there lunges at the ball and takes the catch to help his fellow debutant get his debut wicket. Shake of the head from Labuschagne as he heads to the pavilion, 2 short of his half ton.
Paine is welcomed with a bouncer! He sits under it.
Length ball around off, pushed towards mid off.

NOT OUT! Wickets umpire's call. So India keep the review. A length ball around middle and leg, Paine looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. Siraj puts in a very confident appeal but it has been turned down. He though convinves his skipper to go for the DRS. Rahane goes for it at the very last second. The replays show that the ball would've just clipped the leg stump. So, the onfield decision stays but India doesn't lose their review.
Quicker one around middle, worked towads short fine leg.
Flatter and around off, punched wide of the cover fielder for a run.
Floated on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, defended.
Flatter and around middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
On middle, Paine flicks it uppishly towards square leg. Good over from Ashwin.

Huge appeal again but not out says the umpire again. This time Rahane is not going for it. Is there any bat? A length ball around off, coems back in sharply. Green fails to get bat on ball and is hit on the pad. A loud appeal but nothing from the umpire. Rahane clearly says no for the review.
Fuller and around off, flicked towards square leg.
Bouncer on middle, Green ducks under it.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Good length and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for one.
Dot to end! A testing over from Siraj. The last ball is outside off on a length so Paine lets it be. With that, it is Tea on Day 1.
Lovely start! Flatter and outside off, Green thinks of playing at it but decides against it as it zips away.
On middle, blocked.
Floated around middle, pushed towards mid on.
Flatter and around off, worked on the leg side.
Tossed up and around middle and leg, tucked towards the leg side again.
Short and wide outside off but Green finds the cover fielder. A poor ball but Ashwin gets away with it. A maiden to start post Tea.
Shortish and just outside off pushed towards point off the back foot.
Fuller and around middle, driven to mid on.
Another fine drive but for nothing. This time it is towards mid off.
FOUR! And Paine is finally off the mark. A short ball just outside off, Paine swivels and pulls it over square leg for a boundary. Short of a man in form.
Taps the next one gently towards cover-point and calls for a quick run.
Fuller and around off, blocked off the back foot.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, flicked towards short leg fielder uppishly. Pant is asking Jadeja who is at mid-wicket to be ready.
Flatter and outside off, punched wide of the point fielder for one.
On middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up and on middle, kept out.

NOT OUT! And a loud cheer from the crowd as they see the decision flashing on the big screen. That looked a tough call and the umpire believes that the bat has crossed the line when Pant took the bails off. Maybe they have given the benefit of doubt to the batter. Coming to the delivery, it was fuller and around off, Green pushes it towards cover. They go for the single but stop in the middle and then go for it again as the cover fielder throws the ball at the striker's end. Pant takes the bails off. The Indians are not sure as one of them is heard saying he is in on the stumps mic. Replays roll in and the third umpire takes his own time to confirm the decision. A tough call but not out is the decision which the TV umpire comes up with. Rahane is not happy as he is having a word with the umpire. Paine survives a nervy moment.
Length ball around off, bunted down the ground.
Shortish ball around off, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Short of a length outside off, punched to the covers.
Length ball outside off, Green guides it to gully.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Shortish ball to end the over, tucked it towards mid wicket.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Flatter and around middle, tucked towards short leg.
Tossed up and around middle, blocked.
Full and on middle, Paine flicks it wide of the man at mid on for a run.
Flatter and around middle, punched towards cover-point.
On middle, kept out.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball around off, solidly defended by Paine.
Length ball around middle, Paine tucks this one towards mid-wicket.
A fuller length ball this time around off, Paine dabs it towards point.
EDGY! A length ball around off, Paine looks to guide it towards third man but gets an outside edge and Rahane at gully dives to his left and stops it.
Short and wide outside off, Paine cuts but finds backward point.

Huge appeal but turned down! But it was only the bowler who appealed. This one pitched outside off and then turned in nicely to beat the outside edge. Pant took the chance ont he second attempt as Ashwin appealed. Nothing from the umpire and Pant wasn't too sure so Rahane doesn't go for the review. Replay later roll in and it shows no bat. So, a good call from Pant and Rahane.
Full and just outside off, driven nicely but straight to the cover fielder.
On off, blocked.
On middle, Green flicks it towards mid on.
Flatter and around middle, Green goes back to block off the back foot.
A single on the last ball. Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for one. A fine over form Ashwin.
Fullish and outside off, shaping further away. Green shoulders arms.
A length ball outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off for a single.
Fuller and around off, Paine pushes it towards mid off and says a loud no for the run.

EDGY FOUR! Terrific delivery from Siraj. A length ball just around off, shapes away a touch as Paine looks to defend off his front foot. He plays at it with soft hands as the thick outside edge flies past the first slip fielder. It races away to the fence at the third man fence. 150 up with that boundary.
Good running! A fuller one on the pads, Paine tucks it through square leg and scampers back for two. 7 from the over.
Shortish and just outside off, punched towards the cover fielder.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
On middle, Green comes down the track and pushes it down to long on for one.
Tossed up on the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up and around off, this one turns in as Paine tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Darts this one flat and around off, punched towards mid off by Paine.
Outside off on a good length. Green lets it be.
A length ball outside off, Green leaves it alone again. He was caught in two minds there. Siraj though there was some bat as it went to the keeper but Pant wasn't sure again.
Short and wide outside off, cut to deep point for a brace.

OUT! Three reds and Green has to go. Brilliant bowling from Siraj. Full, fast and straight. Green looks to drive with straight bat but misses to get hit plumb in front of the wickets. A loud, loud apppeal and the umpire raises his finger this time. This looks plumb but Green reviews after having a word with his skipper. Let's see if the technology can save him. Replays roll in and well Green has to go as there is no bat involved and the ball is hitting the stumps.
Length ball around off, Cummins blocks it towards point.
Dot to end the successful over. A length ball around middle, worked on the leg side.
Down the leg side. Left alone by Paine.
Flatter and around middle, kept out.
Tossed up and around off, driven towards the cover fielder.
Floated on middle, Paine comes on front foot to defend.
On middle, defended with soft hands towards the leg side.

OUT! TAKEN! Ashwin strikes again and he gets the big wicket of the Australian skipper. Terrific catch down the leg side. Wicket no. 7 goes down now. Ashwin gets his third. A tossed up ball on middle and leg, Paine comes forward and looks to flick but gets an inside edge. Rahane has kept the fielder there for something similar. Vihar is waiting for a chance like this at backward short leg. He gets the chance and does really well to hold onto this sharp catch. Massive, massive wicket.
Length ball around off, blocked.
Fuller and around off, Cummins blocks off his front foot.
On the pads, Cummins clips it to fine leg for a run.
Full and outside off, driven towards cover.
Shortish and around off, punched towards point for nothing.
Play and a miss! A fullish delivery outside off, Starc goes for the drive away from his body to get beaten.
Flatter but outside off, left alone.
On middle, blocked.
Fired on the pads, Cummins pads it away.
Nicely bowled. This one pitches around off and it turns back in. Sharp bounce too as it hits Cummins high on the pad.
Fuller and around off, driven towards the cover fielder.
Flat and around off, kept out off the back foot by Pat.
Bumrah starts with a length ball just around off, pushed towards mid off.
Fuller and outside off, Starc drives it wide of the cover fielder for a run.
A bumper on middle and leg. Cummins sits under it.
Length ball around middle, Cummins tucks it towards mid-wicket and goes to the other end.
FOUR! Whipped nicely from Starc. A fuller one from Bumrah around off and middle, Starc flicks it hard through mid on for a boundary.
Edgy! A fuller ball outside off, Starc looks to tonk it on the leg side but gets a thick outside edge that goes to third man. Starc gets two more. 8 off the over.
Fired outside off, Cummins lets it be.
Very full and on middle, worked on the leg side.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked with soft hands.
Flatter and around middle, tucked towards backward square leg.
Fuller and around off, blocked off the front foot by Cummins. Another maiden from Ashwin.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and it is Bumrah now who picks his 3rd wicket. A sharp bumper to Starc who looks to take it on and goes for the pull but ends up getting a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards fine leg. Siraj there settles under it and takes first catch of his Test career. India all over Australia here.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Outside off on a length, Cummins lets it be.
A bumper to Cummins but he is not going to take it on as he sits under it.
Nicely bowled. A sharp short ball on the body. Cummins somehow manages to fend it off towards fine leg. Gets two.
Around off on a length, defended back to the bowler. 2 runs and wicket from this Bumrah over.
Fuller and around off, worked toward the leg side.
Tosses it down the leg side, Lyon goes for the sweep but misses.
Shortish and just around off, Lyon punches it towards cover.
Sweeps this one from outside off and opens his account as the ball goes to deep square leg. A bit of giggle from Pant from behind the stumps.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
FOUR! Slogged! Enough of blocking says Cummins and reaches out to the loppy ball outside off and slams it over mid on for a boundary.
Sharp bumber! It is on middle and leg and Lyon wants a piece of it as he goes for the pull but he misses.
Length ball outside off, punched towards mid on.
FOUR! Nicely done! Useful runs. Shortish and just outside off, Lyon cuts it hard and beats the gully fielder's dive to his right. A fine shot.
Full toss outside off, driven towards the cover fielder.
Punched nicely for two. Length ball outside off, it is punched wide of the man at mid off for a brace.
Bouncer and Lyon goes for the pull but mistimes it towards square leg.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid off for a single.
Flatter and around off, Lyon keeps it out off his back foot.
Around off, some turn away as Lyon looks to defend but ends up getting it off the outer half. A single as the ball goes towards vacant short third man.
Beaten! Tossed up and around off, it pitches and turns away and bounces too. Cummins comes on the front foot to block but is beaten.
On off, this time Cummns is right behind the line to defend.
Flatter and around middle, kept out.
Fullish ball on the stumps, driven straight to mid on.
A length ball outside off edges towards the gap at third man for a couple.
SIX! BANG! A bumper but it is down the leg side. Lyon swivels and nails it over fine leg for a maximum.
FOUR! A boundary now as Bumrah's short ball outside off is pumped over mid-wicket for a boundary. The stand moves to 27 off just 27 balls.

OUT! No willow there and it is Umpire's Call on Wickets Hitting So, he has to go. 9 down and Bumrah has 4. After getting hit for a six and a boundary on back of a length ball, Bumrah lands this one on a good length and makes it to come back in as Lyon looks for a drive but misses to get hit on the pad.

FOUR! Hazlewood is off the mark with a boundary. Bumrah looks for a yorker but ends up bowling it down the leg side. Hazlewood tickles it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary. End of an eventful over.
Floated around off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja gets the last man. A fine catch from Siraj. A floated ball around middle, Cummins looks for the slog but ends up getting a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards long on. Sirak settles underneath and takes the catch easily. Australia have been bowled out for 195.
Starc is right on the money! A length ball around off and middle, a touch of inward movement but Agarwal does really well to block it off his front foot.

Huge appeal for LBW but the umpire turns it down. Looks like there was some bat and height looks to be an issue too. They don't take the review. Good length ball just outside off, Agarwal looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. They all go up in a loud appeal but nothing from the umpire. Replays roll in and it shows a big inside edge.
Lovely delivery again. A yorker around off, Agarwal did really well to get his foot out of the way and then block it out.
Good length and around off, Agarwal is right behind the line of the ball to block.
In the channel outside off, Agarwal doesn't flirt with it.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Starc has struck early and Agarwal fails again. Lovely stuff from Starc and he is pumped up. A good length ball just around off, comes back in just a touch as Agarwal looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal and the finger is raised. Agarwal is not too sure if he has got any bat but he goes for the review. Replays roll in and it shows that the ball has hit the pad first. Ball Tracker shows it to be umpire's call on hitting the wickets. So, Agarwal has to go. India keep their review though but a horrid start again for India.
Wide outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
A ripper from Cummins now. A length ball just outside off, Gill pokes at it but makes no connection.
Another lovely delivery. This one pitches around off and jags back in. Gill looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Beaten! Lovely stuff from Cummins. This one pitches on a good length and then kicks off as Gill pokes at it to get beaten.
Beaten again! Gill feels for it again as this one is full and outside off. Once again Gill makes no connection as the ball goes past the outside edge.
A maiden from Cummins as on the last ball, Gill gets behind the line to keep it out.
Length and around off, Pujara forces it on the off side.
Pujara is beaten now! A length ball just outside off, shapes away as Pujara pokes at it.
Fullish and around off, a solid block from Pujara this time.
Shortish and just outside off, Pujara hides his bat and allows the ball to go to the keeper.
Length and outside off, kept out.
Starc goes past the bat again. Consecutive maidens for him. Just outside off on a good length, Pujara has to play at it. He does that off the back foot but is beaten.
Length ball around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Absolute beauty! Nothing much Gill can do about it. A length delivery around off, the batter has to play at it. Gill does that but is beaten.
Shortish and around off, poked towards the gully fielder.

FOUR! Gill is off the mark in style! That is some stroke to get off the mark in Test cricket. A fuller ball around off, Gill drives it through mid off. The fielder gives it a chase but fails to cut if off. This should calm Gill's nerves out in the middle.
Back of a length and around off, blocked off the back foot.

Put down! Gill gets a life. Cummins runs in and bowls this full and around off, Gill looks to flick but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes to Labuschagne at third slip. It is to his right. He gets both his hands but fails to hold onto it.
FOUR! Crunched! Fine shot from Gill again. Short and wide outside off. Gill pounces on the width outside off and nails it through point for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Short and wide outside off, pushed towards point.
Nicely done! A length ball just around off, Gill waits for the ball and then taps it wide of the gully fielder. Two taken before backward point can get to the ball.
WOW! What a ripper! You just can't play these. Unplayable delivery. This one is pitched around off on a good length, it pitches and then shapes away a touch to beat the poke of Gill.
Full and wide, Gill thinks to play the booming drive through the off side but opts against it at the last second.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid on.
This one comes back in after pitching around middle. Pujara looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad.
This time Pujara goes on the back foot to block it out nicely.
Fuller and around off, worked on the leg side.
FOUR! Pujara is up and running with a fine shot. A fuller ball around middle, Pujara waits for the ball to come closer to him and then he just punches the drive through mid on.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball around off, Gill hangs his bat in defense but the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
Goes wide outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
Back of a length and around off, pushed towards point.

FOUR! TAKE THAT! Starc bangs it short and it is on middle, Gill rocks back and powerfully pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary. Wanted to leave it alone at first but went with the shot and fetched a boundary for himself.
Very full and around off, kept out.

FOUR! Another boundary for Gill. Starc runs in and dishes the full ball on the pads. The Indian batters love it there. Gill flicks it to the right side of the mant at fine leg. The fielder tries to cut it off but fails to do so.
Length ball around off, worked on the leg side for a run.
Length ball outside off, guides it to the right of gully where Green stops it.
Shortish ball on middle, defended straight back by Gill.
Lovely timing! A fuller length ball on the stumps, Giill drives it gloriously past mid off to take 3 more runs as Wade from mid off chases and keeps the ball in play.
A big bumper which goes well over Pujara. He ducks under it.
Shortish and around off, tapped towards point for a single.
Length ball down the leg side, Pujara lets it be.
A length ball around off, Pujara taps it towards covers and runs but goes back after his partner says no.
Fuller length ball on the pads, Pujara misses the flick and gets hit on the pads. A slight appeal from the Australian players but nothing from the umpire.
Beaten! A good length ball outside off stump, Pujara looks to play at it but gets beaten. That was a trademark Hazlewood delivery right in the corridor of uncertainty.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Tight first over from Hazlewood. Shortish and around off, Pujara stays back to push it towards the cover region. Josh will have to bowl this one again as the TV umpire has called it a no ball.
Full and around off, kept out.
Full and just outside off to begin, Gill drives it through covers and gets a brace.
Floated around off, Gill comes on the front foot to defend.
FOUR! Drilled! Full and around off, Gill comes down the track and creams it through mid off and bags another boundary.
On off, watchfully defended.
Floated full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Tossed up and around off, Gill comes on the front foot to block.

Confusion but safe in the end. A length ball around off, Pujara pushes it towards point and goes for a run. Gill sends him back. The fielder has a shy but he misses. There is no one to do back up as the ball goes towards deep mid-wicket and they eventually get the single.
Risky leave! A length ball, this one is just outside off, Gill covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper. It wasn't too far away from the off pole.
Length ball outside off, easy leave this time.
Shortish and just outside off, pushed towards point by Gill. Last 2 balls coming up.
Hesitation again but safe again. A length ball around off and middle, Gill pushes it wide of the man at mid on and calls for a single. He takes a few step forward but Pujara sends him back.
A fullish ball around off, Gill comes on the front foot and blocks it solidly. With this solid block, it is Stumps on Day 1.

Huge appeal but it has been turned down! Action on the first ball of Day 2. A good length ball just around off, it moves away just a touch as it goes past Pujara's poke. It goes behind and Paine takes the catch and appeals. The umpire turns down. Paine though is confident and he takes the appeal upstairs. Replays roll in and Hot Spot shows nothing. RTS has a little murmur but it is not enough for the TV umpire to overturn the onfield call. Pujara stays and Australia lose the review. What a start though.
Good length ball outside off, guided down to gully.
Length ball on the stumps, defended solidly by Pujara.
Length ball around off, defended towards short leg.
A good length ball outside off, left alone.
A length ball around off defended solidly.
Length ball on middle, Gill misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
A length ball outside off, left alone.

Dropped! Paine puts down a chance. A length ball around off, it comes back in sharply as Gill plays at it away from his body. He gets an inside edge. The ball goes to the left of the keeper but Paine fails to hold on.
FOUR! LOVELY SHOT! A fullish ball around middle, Gill flicks this one through mid- wicket to get a boundary.
Length ball way outside off, Gill lets it be.
A length ball around off, defended solidly.
Length ball around off, Pujara block this out.
Just short! A length ball outside off, Pujara gets the edge, but the ball doesn't carry to first slip.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
A short bumper on the body, Pujara ducks under it.
Length ball around off, defended solidly.
Fullish ball around off, played towards covers by Pujara.
FOUR! EDGY! A length ball around off, Gill gets an inside edge, the ball misses the stumps and also Paine to run away towards the fiine leg boundary.
A fullish ball outside off, Gill drives it handsomely through the covers and they run 3 before the fielder returns the ball.
A length ball around middle, Pujara plays it down towards mid- wicket.
Drifting down the pads, Pujara tucks this away towards square leg and they run 3.
A fullish length just around off, blocked solidly by Gill.
Similar ball around off, Gill is solid in his defense.
Bouncer on middle, Pujara does well to duck under it.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
Length delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it through square leg for a couple.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Pujara looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Back of a length on middle, Pujara keeps it out.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Pujara looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Gill defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Gill flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Length delivery outside off, Pujara offers no shot to this one.
Back of a length on middle, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket again.
What a ripper to end! How did that miss the bat? A length ball around off, comes back in a touch as Pujara pokes at it but is beaten for inside edge.
Length ball just outside off, poked towards the man at gully.
A bumper on middle, Gill sits under it.
Super shot but for no runs! A fullish ball around off, Gill hits it hard and straight back to the bowler. Cummins gets down quickly to stop the ball.
Play and a miss! Goes for the expansive drive through the covers as Cummins bowls this full and wide. Makes no connection does Gill.
Short and wide outside off, punched towards the man at backward point.
Back of a length and around off, solidly blocked off the back foot by Gill.
Full and just wide outside off, Pujara lets it be.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave for Pujara.
Shortish length ball around off, Pujara blocks this out on the on side.
A good length ball on middle, Pujara looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
Length ball outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Fullish ball around off, Pujara dabs it softly towards gully.

EDGY FOUR! Credit to Gill for playing with soft hands though. Length ball around off, Gill looks to defend but gets an outside edge that goes between second slip and gully and into the third man fence. Frustrating for the Aussies.
Sharp bumper around off, Gill drops his hands and allows it to go to the keeper.
Shortish and just around off, pushed towards the man at point off the back foot.
Back of a length and around off, defended towards the cover fielder this time.
Another short ball, punched towards cover for nothing.
A solid back foot block to the last ball of the over from Gill.
A short ball to begin from Green. It is outside off, easy for Pujara to get out of the way.
Full and on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball just outside off, moves away a touch as Pujara shoulders arms.
Landed outside off on a shortish length. Pujara makes another leave.

Was that a chance? A fuller ball on middle and leg, Pujara flicks it uppishly. The ball goes to the left of the leg gully fielder who dives to his left but it goes away from him. Two taken before fine leg can get around.

Edged but short. The Indians are riding their luck at the moment. A length ball just outside off, Pujara pokes at it with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge but falls short of the man at first slip.
Good length and around off, blocked.
On the pads, flicked to deep square leg for one.
Full and outside off, driven nicely by Pujara but straight to the cover fielder.
Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball hits his pad and goes to fine leg for a leg bye.

OUT! TAKEN! Cummins finally gets his man. A lose shot from Gill and this time he runs out of his luck. He wanted to go after Cummins here but falls in the process. Lovely from Cummins. He deserves this wicket. Fuller and outside off, Gill looks to go for the big booming drive through the covers but he ends up nicking it behind. A simple chance for Paine behind the sticks. Paine will not make any mistake. Australia get the breakthrough they were after. A fine knock from Gill but he would feel he has thrown away a top start.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point and a loud call for no.
A bumper outside off, Pujara ducks.
In the channel outside off, Pujara covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Length and around off, worked wide of the man at mid on for one.
Full and around off, Rahane pushes it towards the cover region.
Outside off on a good length. Left alone.
Length ball around off, blocked on the leg side.
Full and outside off, Pujara this time leans and pushes it through the covers. Returns for a brace easily.
Just outside off on a good length, Pujara covers his sticks and allows it to go to the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT! A stunner of a catch from Paine and Australia get the massive wicket of Pujara. It is that man Cummins again. Huge, huge wicket. Lovely bowling from Cummins again. It pitches just around off and it moves just a hint. Pujara looks to defend but gets an outside edge. The ball goes to the right side of Paine. It is in front of the first slip fielder but Paine dives to his right and the ball sticks in his hand. A superb take from the Aussie skipper as it would have fallen short of the slip fielder again. Credit to Cummins as well for steaming in, in this extended spell and he has got the reward for bowling in the right line and length.
In the channel outside off to the new man. Vihari shoulders arms.
Vihari is off the mark with a good stroke! A fuller ball around off, he strokes it through mid off. Labuschagne chases it down with a slide near the long off fence. Three taken.
Fuller and around off and middle, flicked to mid on.
Length ball around off, blocked.
Shortish and around middle and leg, Vihari looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad.
Shortish and around middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Wide outside off, easy leave for Vihari.
A maiden from Green. The last ball is short but outside off so Vihari lets it go again.
Fuller and outside off, Rahane lets it go to the keeper.
In the channel again, Rahane allows it to go to the keeper.
Edged but doesn't carry, AGAIN! Fullish ball just outside off, Rahane this time looks to defend but gets an outside edge but the ball falls short of the man at third slip.
Gets behind the line of the ball this time to defned it on the off side.
Outside off on a length, left alone.
Driven nicely but for nothing. Another maiden from Cummins. Full and outside off, Rahane drives it well but finds mid off.
Outside off on a length. Vihari shoulders arms.
Edgy! Full and outside off, Vihari looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge through gully. Three taken before the fielder can chase it down.
Just outside off on a good length, Rahane covers his stumps and allows it to go to the keeper.

Huge appeal but it is turned down! No review from Australia as Paine suggests it would go over the stumps. A length ball around off, it sharply comes back in and beats the bat of Rahane. He is struck high on the pad and the Aussies appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Outside off, left alone.
Good drive again but no run again. Full and around off, driven to the left of the man at mid off who doesn't let it go past him.
In the channel outside off to begin, Vihari lets it go to the keeper.
Around off on a length, kept out.
In the channel again, Vihari lets it go.
Good leave! This one is fuller and just outside off, Vihar lets it go again. The ball tails back in but does so after going past the stick.
Very full ball outside off, blocked.
A maiden to begin from Starc. A very full ball around off and middle, Vihari pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length outside off, left alone by Rahane.
A length ball on the pads, Rahane looks to tuck but get hits on the pad and they take a leg bye as the ball goes towards the leg side.
FOUR! Classy stuff this from Vihari. A fullish ball on the stumps, Vihari flicks this one towards mid-wicket boundary to collect four.
Length ball on the stumps, tucked away on the leg side.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Fullish delvery on the pads, Vihari flicks it in the gap at mid-wicket to collect a brace as the mid on fielder chases it.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball around off, pushed towards covers.
Rahane is off the mark on the 17th ball. A bouncer down the leg side, Rahane pulls it down to fine leg for one.
A low full toss on the pads, Vihari misses his flick and they collect a leg bye.
Length ball around middle, tucked it towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball around off, blocked solidly by Vihari.
Short of a length outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Fullish ball around off, Rahane trods forward and blocks it.
Length ball around off, played straight towards mid on.
Fuller length outside off, Rahane comes forward and leaves.
A good length just outside off, Rahane is not interested in playing that.
Length ball around off, Rahane blocks it out solidly.
A length ball angling across Vihari, left alone.
Length ball around off, Vihari shoulders arms to it.
Fullish ball around off, Vihari drives it straight to covers.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Yorker length ball on the pads, Vihari misses his flick and they take a leg bye. Loud appeal from Starc, but the Umpire is not interested neither is Paine convinced to go for the review.
Full and on the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Fullish and around off, Rahane comes on the front foot to keep it out.
Back of a length and around off, Rahane gets on his back foot to block.
Full and on the pads, clipped to fine leg for one.
Fuller and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Little too wide outside off, easy leave.
Bouncer on middle. Vihari ducks.
Length ball around off, kept out.
Length ball around off, Rahane comes on the front foot to defend.

FOUR! Streaky boundary for Rahane. A length ball around off, the ball pitches and then moves away as Rahane looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. It goes past the gully fielder and into the third man fence.
Full and on middle, flicked on the leg side.
A full ball outside off, Rahane looks to drive but misses and the ball goes through to Paine.
Another fuller ball but this time Rahane is not chasing after it as he shoulders arms.
A floated fuller ball around off, Vihari comes on the front foot and pushes it back to the bowler.
Comes down the track does Vihari and looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get struck on the pad.
This time he stays inside the crease, a big stride forward and a solid defense.
On middle, worked on the leg side.
Looks to come down the track again but this time Lyon bowls it flat. Vihari adjusts well and tucks it on the leg side.
Flatter and on middle again, Vihari keeps it out. Maiden to start from Lyon.
Short and wide outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Length ball just outside off, pushed towards mid off by Rahane.
Sharp short of a length ball just around off, it is angling away. Rahane sways out of the line.
Full but outside off, Rahane covers the stumps and allows it to Paine behind.
On the pads and Rahane flicks it wide of the mid-wicket fielder who chases it down. Two taken before he can get to the ball.
Fuller and outside off, Rahane squeezes it out towards gully where the fielder does well to stop the ball to his right.
Down the leg side. Left alone.
On middle, tucked on the leg side.
Tossed up and around off and middle, Vihar blocks it off the front foot.
Floated on middle, this time Vihari works it wide of the man at mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
On middle, Rahane is solid in defense.

Full and around off, turns in a touch as Rahane looks to defend. He gets it off the inner half. The ball goes just to the right of the forward short leg fielder. Wasn't too far but Rahane survives. With that, it is Lunch on Day 2.
Hazlewood starts with a length ball outside off which shapes away further outside off. Vihari lets it go to the keeper.
Slightly fuller but still wide enough for Vihar to play.
Outside off on a good length again, Vihari shoulders arms.
Bowls this length ball on the stumps and Vihari comes on the front foot to block.
Another one around off, Vihari stays back to defend.
A maiden to begin the session from Hazlewood. Length ball around off, Vihari once again is on his toes to defend it.
Flatter ball on the pads, Rahane comes on the front foot to defend but pads it away in the end.
Around off, turning in to Rahane who does well to block.
Fuller and around off, kept out by Rahane off the front foot.
Flatter and outside off, Rahane punches it wide of the man at point and takes a single.
Flat and on middle, worked towards the square leg region for one.
Short and on middle, Rahane goes for the pull but doesn't connect it as well as he would've liked. It goes to the left of Starc at square leg. They take a run.
Fuller ball around off, defended towards covers.
A length ball on middle, Rahane blocks this out.
A length ball around middle, taps it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick run.
Short ball around off stump, Vihari ducks under it.
Fullish ball around middle, defended straight back.
Fuller ball outside off, left alone.
Tossed up and on middle, Rahane flicks it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
On off, Vihari flicks but finds mid-wicket.

FOUR BYES! That beats everyone. Tossed up just outside off, it pitches, bounces extra and turns way down the leg side. No chance for Paine to stop that as it races down to the fine leg fence for four byes.
Shortish and on middle, Vihari nudges it towards square leg for a single. 100 up for India with that run.
Full and on middle, flicked well but Rahane finds mid on.
Good turn again! Rahane manages to keep it out at the very last moment. This one pitches outside off and turns back in. Rahane is on his back foot and gets his bat down in time to keep it out.
Back of a length and on middle, Vihari gets on his toes to defend.
Good length and around off, defended towards mid on.
Fuller this time around middle and leg, flicked towards fine leg for a single.
Short of a length around off, Rahane pulls it towards fine leg for another single.
Fuller length on middle, Vihari blocks this one on the on side.
Dot to end the over. A length ball outside off, left alone.
Floated on middle, Rahane looks to defend but it goes to leg slip off the inner half.
Around off stump, Rahane prods forward to defend it.
Flaoted around middle, Rahane plays it back to the bowler.
On middle, pushed to mid on for a quick single.
Flat and on middle, tucked to square leg for nothing.
Pitches outside off, turns in again as Vihari looks to work it on the leg side. The ball hits his pad and goes over leg gully fielder. Two leg byes taken.
No ball! A length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be. The third umpire from upstairs calls it a no ball.
FOUR! Banged short and Rahane says I am ready for that. He swivels and nails the pull down to the deep square leg fence. Fine shot.
A jaffa from Hazlewood. Good comeback from him. Shortish and around off, it shapes away nicely as it gets close to the bat of Rahane who looks to defend. Lucky not to edge.
Works the next one through square leg to get to the other end.
Fuller and just outside off, defended towards the cover region.
Uppish but safe! Back of a length ball on middle, Vihari goes for the pull. He doesn't go full swing and it goes wide of the fine leg fielder for one.
Dot to end! In the channel outside off, Rahane allows it to go to the keeper. 7 from the over.
Floated around off, Vihari sweeps but finds backward square leg.
Shortish around off, tucked away towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Shot! Fine shot from Vihari. A flatter ball outside off, Vihari stays back, waits for the ball to get closer and then cuts it through short third man for a boundary. It brings up the 50-run stand between the two.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lyon strikes! Vihari wanted to dominate the spinner but falls in the process. Lyon wins the battle. A tossed up ball on middle, Vihari winds up and goes for the slog sweep but the ball bounces extra and takes the gloves. It balloons to the left of the keeper. The first slip fielder, Smith, calls for the catch and takes it easily. They appeal and the finger is raised. Lyon gets his man and breaks the blooming stand. Shake of the head as Vihari walks back. India needed him to continue. India still behind 79.
Darted outside off, Pant shoulders arms.
Another one which is bowled outside off, Pant lets it be again. End of a successful over from Lyon.
Good length ball around middle, Rahane block this out.
Length ball around off, guided it towards gully.
Short ball on middle, Rahane sways away from it. Hazlewood gives a stare!
Fuller length ball on the pads, flicked away towards square leg for a single.
Good length ball angling across Pant, he lets it be.
Bumper to end the over. A short ball on the body, Pant ducks under it.
Tossed up around middle, turning in, tucked on the leg side by Rahane.
Rahane comes down the track and covers the spin and pushes it towards mid on for one.

Edgy! Pant is off the mark in a streaky fashion! Tossed up again and this one is full. It turns away as Pant comes on the front foot to defend. It takes the outside edge and goes past Smith at first slip. He gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
Lands outside off and turns away as Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Short and wide, Pant cuts it to cover-point and takes a run.
Flat and around off, Rahane pushes it towards short third man and gets to the other end.
A ripper! Landed just around off and then shaped away. Rahane looks to defend off his toes but misses.
Short of a length outside off, dabs it towards point.
Fuller ball in the channel outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Shortish outside off, pulled down to mid-wicket.
Fuller ball around middle, Rahane blocks this out on the front foot.
Good length ball around off, defended solidly.
Wide outside off, pushed towards the cover region.
Short and wide, Pant cuts it hard but finds cover-point.
Lands on middle and turns in. Pant nudges it to fine leg and takes two.
Floated around off, Pant punches it to mid off and gets to the other end.
Rahane skips down the track and flicks it down to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up around off, Pant keeps it out with a solid front foot defense.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Shortish ball outside off, Rahane stands tall and punches this through the covers for a brace.
Length ball outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
A fuller length around middle, defended solidly on the off side.
Rahane drives this through the covers for another couple as Labuschagne chases the ball and returns it back.

FOUR! Nicely done by Rahane! A good over for the Indians as they get 8 off it. Cummins bowls a very full ball outside off, Rahane squeezes it between gully and the slip cordon. The ball races away to the third man fence.
Tossed up and outside off, turning away. Pant lets it be.
And again! Pant lets it be once again.
This time he pushes it wide of the short cover fielder for one.
Floated on middle, defended back to the bowler.
On middle, kept out by Rahane off the front foot.
Dot to end! Flatter and around middle and leg, Rahane stays back and defends it out.
Full and around off, Pant drives it down the ground. He fails to connect it sweetly but it goes towards long off. Two taken.
This time he hits it wide of the cover fielder. Two more before the mid off fielder can get to the ball.
FOUR! A boundary now! Pat runs in and bangs it short and bowls it on middle, Pant swivels and nails the pull in front of square for a boundary. Super shot. 8 off the first 3 balls.
Cummins returns back to bowling in the channel outside off now and Pant says I am not playing at these.

FOUR! Through the off side. Pant bags another boundary. A fuller ball outside off, Pant goes for the drive. It is not off the middle but it goes wide of the backward point fielder for a boundary. The deficit now is under 50.
A fullish ball wide of the crease from Cummins, Pant pushes it towards the cover region. Excellent over for the Indians.
Full and on middle and leg, Rahane comes down the track and pokes it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full and around off, blocked off the front foot.
FOUR! Slammed away! Pant is in mood here as he bags another boundary. Short and just outside off, Pant rocks back and flays it through the covers for a boundary. 150 is up for the Indians.
Short and wide again, Pant cuts it hard again. This time the cover-point fielder runs to his left and keeps it down to a run.
On middle, Rahane defends it out off his front foot.
Shortish and outside off, turns back in as Rahane tucks it towards short fine leg.
In the channel outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Another one wide outside off, Pant has no business with it as he shoulders arms.
One more leave as Cummins continues to bowl in the channel. He is not giving away anything in this over here.
Cummins bends his back and this time goes for a bumper but the line is down the leg side. Pant ducks easily.
Gets the line to the bumper right. Pant sways away from the line. Good over from Cummins so far. Pant has responded well too as he has kept himself calm and has not gone after him.
Fuller and on middle, Pant flicks this time but finds mid on. A maiden from Cummins after going for 12 in his previous over.
Short and outside off, gets a bottom edge and almost chops it on.
Floated around middle, tucked on the on side.
Short on the body, Rahane pulls this one past fine leg to collect a couple, where Wade collects the ball and stops the boundary.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Turning in from outside off from a shortish length. Rahane keeps it out.

A couple to end the over! It pitches outside off again and turns in. Not too much as Rahane looks to cut but it bounces extra. The India skipper manages to guide it fine towards third man for a brace.
Wide outside off on a length, easily left alone by Pant.
Length ball wide outside off, Pant lets it be.
Fuller ball around off, Pant drives it to the covers.
Fuller ball around off, Pant hits it straight back to the bowler, Cummins there picks the ball in his follow through and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Good fielding there by Cummins.
Banged short and Pant pulls it through mid-wicket. Deep square leg fielder gets around but not before Pant adds two more to his name.

Chance but Green misses to hold on! Cummins lures Pant with a fuller ball outside of, Pant goes after it and it flies off the outer half towards Green at gully. He dives to his left, sticks out his one hand but it doesn't stick. Two taken as the ball goes to deep point.
Good length and just around off, poked towards point.
Length ball around middle, worked on the leg side for nothing.
FOUR! A freebie from Green! A friendly full toss, Rahane just pushes it down the ground. Just timed it and it raced to the long on fence. The skipper moves into the 40s.
A front foot block to follow the boundary.
On the pads, worked down to deep square leg for one. Another 50-run stand for India.
Pant batting way out of his crease makes a solid front foot defense on the last ball.
Wide outside off to begin, Rahane lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller and around middle, flicked to mid-wicket.

Shot! Fine shot! Fuller and around off, Rahane comes on the front foot and pushes it through the covers. Just a mere push. The cover fielder chases it down. Three taken as Labuschagne makes a sliding stop.
A yorker on middle, Pant jams it down.
Length ball on the pads, Pant flicks it down to deep square leg for one.
Single on the last ball as Rahane pushes it wide of the cover fielder. They wanted the second but opted against it in the end.
Short ball outside off, Rahane lets it go. It was good bumper which Paine jumps and collects.
Around off on a length, pushed towards point.
Good yorker but Rahane is up for it as he keeps it out easily.
A length ball in the channel outside off, left alone.
Short ball on middle, Rahane pulls this one through the gap at deep mid-wicket and collects a couple.
A length ball just around off, pushed towards covers. Rahane has to wait for his 50.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A poor, poor short from Pant and he throws it away. Starc gets the timely breakthrough. Short and just wide outside off, Pant throws his bat as he looks to cut but ends up getting a tickle behind. Paine accepts the catch and celebrates. It wasn't that wide but Pant wanted a peice of it but he falls in the process. 250th Test wicket for Starc. A good, little hand though from Pant. India still behind 22.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, blocked off the front foot by Jadeja.
Length ball around off, Jadeja defends off his back foot.
Outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.

Nicely punched and Jadeja gets three to open his account. Fuller and around off, Jadeja meets it with straight bat and pushes it through mid off. The fielder from the ring chases it down. Three taken. Successful over from Starc.
Shortish ball on the body, Jadeja dabs it towards the slips.
Another short one on the body, Jadeja ducks under it.
Short of a length around off,  Jadeja sways away from it.
Shortish ball on leg, dabs it down on the on side.
Another one of those short balls on the body, Jadeja ducks again.
Good over this from Cummins. A shortish ball but down the leg, Jadeja leaves it alone.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR RAHANE! The skipper is leading the charge for the Indians here. A fine knock from him. There were murmurs regarding his form with the bat but he has played a well-compiled knock to put all the talks to rest. Can he take India to a stronger position from here? He got a superb hundred in the 2014/15 tour and would be eager to do something similar here. He gets to his half ton by flicking the fuller ball on his pads down to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one wide outside off, easily allowed it to go to the keeper.
One more leave as Starc continues to bowl in the channel.
FOUR BYES! Starc goes for the yorker but bowls it down the leg side. Rahane fails to flick it. Paine dives to his left but fails to collect the ball.
Full and outside off, pushed towards point.
Short of a length, Jadeja dabs it towards point for a run.
Short ball angling into Rahane, who ducks under it.
A good length ball around off, pushed on the off side.
Fuller length ball around middle, Rahane defends it solidly.
A good length ball around off, a bit of inswing, Rahane blocks this one on the on side.
Full ball on middle, Rahane flicks it towards square leg.
Down the leg side. Jadeja looks to flick but misses.
FOUR BYES! Starc is trying to rattle Jadeja with the bumper on the body but on this one he does little too much. It goes wide of leaping Paine and into the fine leg fence.
Sharp again from Starc. This one is around off, Jadeja hops and keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, kept out off the front foot.
Banged short and Jadeja says enough is enough. He rocks back and pulls it wide of the man at mid on. Three taken before the fielder can get to the ball.
Good length and around off, Jadeja pushes it towards the off side and thinks for a run but Rahane sends him back.
Back of a length and around off, it keeps low as Jadeja is hit on the pad. They appeal but nothing from the umpire. Clearly a big inside edge on this one.
A short ball on middle, Jadeja ducks.
Fuller and around off, Jadeja looks to flick but gets a leading edge back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Jadeja blocks off the back foot.
Bumper on middle, Jadeja takes it on and pulls it wide of the fine leg fielder.
Length ball around off, Jadeja pushes it towards the off side crosses for a quick single.
Fuller and around off, Rahane blocks.
STREAKY FOUR! A length ball just around off. It shapes away. Rahane plays it very late and runs it down to the third man fence. India take the lead with that boundary.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point.

Appeal for caught behind down the leg side but nothing from the umpire. A fuller ball down the leg side, Rahane misses his flick. Paine dives to his right and collects the ball. He appeals but not out says the umpire.
Another one down the leg side and Rahane misses his flick again.
Length ball angling across, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Short of a length on middle, blocked solidly.
Shortish around middle, Jadeja dabs it on the on side.
A length ball in the corridor outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to it.
A short bumper on the body, Jadeja ducks under it.
Maiden from Hazlewood. A short ball this time around off, Jadeja has no business playing with it.
Good length angling across, Rahane leaves it alone.
Beaten! A length ball around off, held its line and Rahane tries to defend but is beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller ball but way outside off, left alone.
Shortish ball on the body, Rahane stands tall and bunts it down.

EDGY FOUR! Lucky for Rahane! A length ball outside off, Rahane flirts with it as he stays rooted to his crease. An outside edge is induced but it flies between the keeper and Smith who is at the second slip. Rahane into the 60s. 200 up for the visitors. The lead now reads 7.
Length ball to finish the over, outside off stump and left alone.
Length ball around off, blocked by Jadeja.
Three more! Again not from the middle of Jadeja's bat. A length ball outside off, Jadeja plays at it away from his body. The ball flies through gully and they take three.
