Short of a length on the body, Rahane tucks it on the on side.
Shortish ball around middle, Rahane pulls this one towards deep square leg for a single.
Length ball outside off, Jadeja pushes this one at cover.
Fuller ball this time but down the leg side, Jadeja misses his flick and the keeper dives and stops the ball.
Fuller length around off, Rahane pushes this one towards covers.
Fuller ball angling in the pads, Rahane flicks this one wide towards mid on.
Length ball on middle, Rahane comes forward and defends it.
A couple now to Rahane. A short ball outside off, Rahane punches this one through the covers and collects a couple.
Length ball angling across, Rahane leaves it alone.
Good leave by Rahane, A length ball outside off, Rahane does not tinker with it.
Shortish outside off, Jadeja punches this one towards point.
A length ball outside off, driven by Jadeja to the covers.
Fuller this time angling around middle, Jadeja plays it with a straight bat towards mid on.
A drive enticing ball outside off, Jadeja leaves it.
Short ball around leg stump, Jadeja ducks under it.
A length ball around off, Jadeja dabs it towards gully.

He starts with a shortish ball outside off, Rahane punches it to the left of the cover fielder who dives that side but fails to stop. The point fielder runs to get to the ball. Enough time for Rahane to take two more.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! DRILLED! Stunning stroke! Lyon tosses it up, Rahane jumps out of the crease and nails the drive through the covers. Cummins gives it a chase till the ropes, dives and tries to stop but misses.
Floated around middle, pushed back to Lyon.
Shortish and around off, Rahane goes back to block it out. 6 off Lyon's over.
Full ball down the leg side. Jadeja misses his flick.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Outside off, watchfully left alone.
Fuller and around middle, Jadeja stays back to block.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length on the body, Jadeja nudges it towards square leg and takes a quick single.
Tossed up outside off, Jadeja lets it go. The ball turned sharply after pitching.
Jadeja punches it through the covers for a single.
Floated around middle, tucked towards square leg for a run.
Floated ball around off, jadeja leaves it alone, was close to the off stump.
Flatter around off, blocked by Jadeja.
Fuller ball on middle, swept away towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! SHOT! Short and wide outside off, Jadeja slams it through backward point and bags a boundary.
Pushes the next fuller one towards mid off for one. And the single brings up yet another 50-run stand.
Landed around off on a length, pushed towards the off side.
Outside off, a leave from Rahane.
Another one well outside off, Rahane is not playing at it.
Short and just outside off, Rahane looks to cut but misses.
Tossed up and outside off, turning away. Jadeja lets it be.
Beaten by the flight. A tossed up ball around off, Jadeja looks to defend but gets beaten. That was a beautiful ball from Lyon.
Floated around middle, tucked towards fine leg for single.
Tossed up around off, tucked away towards backward square leg.
Slightly short on the stumps, played straight back.
Floated on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket. Good over from Lyon.
Full and on middle, flicked wide of the man at mid on for a quick single.
Fullish ball outside off, driven nicely but straight to mid off.
Length ball outside off, shouldered arms by Rahane.
A fuller length this time outside off swings away, Rahane leaves it alone.
Shortish ball on the stumps, Rahane bunts this on the off side.
Fuller length around off, Rahane pushes this one towards cover.
Short and wide outside off, Jadeja cuts but can't go past the backward point fielder.
Tossed up around off, Jadeja comes on the front foot to block.
Short again, punched towards mid off.
Floated full and around off, Jadeja pushes it towards gully and thinks for a single but is sent back.
Tossed up and outside off, turning away. A leave from Jadeja.
Another short ball outside off, Jadeja finds cover again. A maiden from Lyon.
Full around off, driven to mid off.
Another fine shot but nothing again. Full and wide outside off, Rahane drives but the cover fielder makes a diving stop to his left.
Short and on middle, pulled down to fine leg for a run.
Bumper to Jadeja now but it goes well over.
In the channel outside off, a leave from Jadeja.
Flicks the next one through mid-wicket and gets two.
Full and on middle, flicked wide of the man at mid on for a single.
Nice short. Wide outside off from Lyon. It has been the line he is bowling from the last two overs. This time Jadeja crunches it through backward point for three.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
Tosses it up and Rahane is on the front foot to defend.
Another loopy ball around off, kept out by Rahane.
Tossed up and around off, a big stride forward and Rahane is solid on the front foot.
A fuller one on the pads of Jadeja to beign, he whips it through mid-wicket for three.
Full again, Rahane drives it towards the cover region.

PUT DOWN?. That went really quickly to Smith but it burst through his fingers. A full ball outside off, Rahane looks to squeeze it out but gets it off the outside edge. It goes towards the left of Smith at a good height but he is taken by surprise as it comes quickly to him and he fails to hold on.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Lovely delivery to end the over! Just outside off and angled in, Jadeja pokes at it but misses.
Length ball around off, Rahane dabs it on the off side.
Good length around off, played towards covers.
FOUR! Nicely driven! A fullish ball outside off, Rahane leans on the drive and the ball races past mid off. Marnus chases the ball but loses the race.
Similar length, Similar short, driven nicely down the ground but this time Marnus keeps it to two. Rahane is looking good against the new ball as he is presenting the full face of the bat.
Two more! Short and wide outside off, he punches it through the cover region for a brace now.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Length ball on off, Jadeja taps this towards mid on and takes a quick run. The single brings up the lead to 50.
Good Running this by the two! A length ball around middle, Rahane tucks this one towards fine leg and takes a quick couple of runs. Starc is not happy with the fielder there.
Play and a Miss by Rahane, A fuller length ball outside off, Rahane looks to drive but gets beaten.
Length ball down the leg, Rahane misses his flick.
Short of a length but again down leg, left alone by Rahane.

FOUR! Take that! Short and wide outside off, Rahane hammers it over point and bags another boundary. Runs flowing thick and fast for the Indians now. Rahane moves to 88 with that boundary and India crosses 250.
Length ball around middle, tucks this one towards fine leg for a run.
A length ball around off, Rahane plays it gently past the gully fielder for a single. They think for two but decided against it.
Good length around off angling across, Jadeja withdraws from his defense.
Length ball around middle and leg, Jadeja misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. Huge appeal from the bowler but nothing from the Umpire.
Length ball around middle, tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball around off, defended solidly by Rahane.
A length ball outside off to begin from him, Jadeja lets it be.
Fullish but outside off again, easily left alone.
On the pads, flicked through mid-wicket for a brace by Jadeja.
Outside off again from Josh. Jadeja lets it be.
A bumper now! Jadeja once again sways away and allows for Paine to collect.
A maiden to begin from Hazlewood in his fresh spell but nothing threatening. A length ball outside off, left alone.
Length ball around off, Rahane looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to fine leg for a run.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked through square leg for one.
Stunning stroke but Wade makes an excellent save! Fuller and outside off, Rahane drills the drive but Wade dives to his right to knock it down.
The gully fielder makes a stop now. A shortish ball just outside off, Rahane stays back and forces it to the left of Green at gully who makes a diving stop.
Banged short and Rahane pulls it wide of the man at deep mid-wicket. Two more for Rahane.
Tucked towards the leg side for a single. Rahane will keep the strike for the next over.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.
Length ball around off, Rahane looks to work it on the leg side but the ball takes the outer half and goes towards point.
Three more and Rahane is just a boundary away from a ton! He gets a fuller ball on the pads and flicks it through square leg. Good, aggressive running means they get three.
Just outside off on a good length. A brave leave from Jadeja.
And another leave it is from Jadeja as Josh bowls it wide outside off.
Around off on a length, a solid front foot defense from Rahane.
Around off again, tapped towards gully.
An appeal for LBW but only from behind the wicket. Nothing from Cummins. It comes back in after pitching. Rahane misses to get hit on the pad. Replays show a big inside edge.

FOUR! SHOT! CENTURY FOR RAHANE! What a sensational knock this has been from him! He has batted with ease here. The big pressure of leading India in the absence of  their regular skipper Kohli has not put him under any sort of pressure. If at all it has done anything, it has helped his game. There were questions about his form which has dipped over the past couple of years but he has responded with a superb gritty knock. He gets a loosener from Cummins. Short and wide outside off, Rahane slashes it over point and bags the boundary to get to the milestone. His 12th Test ton. He has repeated his Melbourne heroics form 2014 here and is putting the team in a great position. A sedate celebration from him as he knows that the job his not finished.
Back of a length ball around off, kept out.
Shortish and around off, Rahane manages to fend it off as it bounces extra. Maybe he has taken a blow on the gloves.
Fulller length ball around off, blocked solidly.
Overpitched outside off, squeezed towards point.
Length ball in the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Bumper on the body, Jadeja ducks under it.
Length ball on the stumps, tucked towards square leg for a run.

FOUR! Classy drive this by Rahane. A fuller length ball around off, Rahane creams this drive through the covers. The boundary brings up 100-run stand between the two. This can well be a match-winning stand between the two.
Floated around off, defended back.
Floated around off, defended solidly.
A shortish ball outside off, played towards point.
Tossed up ball on the stumps, blocked solidly.
Short and wide, Jadeja punches this one towards covers.
Again short and wide, played toward deep point for a run.
Length ball around middle, played straight back.
WIDE! Short and way outside off, wided by the umpire.
Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller length ball outside the off stump, Jadeja lets it be.
Fuller ball but way outside off, ignored by Jadeja.
Shortish ball just outside off, Jadeja sways away from it.
Fuller length ball outside off, Jadeja taps it towards deep point for a run.
Full ball outside off, driven to the right of mid off for a run.
Fulller length around off, pushed towards covers.

Put down! Oh, dear, Australia! What is happening? Head cannot believe that he has put it down. Another chance goes begging. A sharp bumper around off, Rahane looks to defend off his toes but he is not in control as it flies to his right off the gloves. Head from point comes running forward and so does Green from gully. Both go for it but Head lunges forward first and then gets both his hands on the ball but as his elbows land on the turf, the ball pops out. A let off for Rahane here.
A good length ball around off to begin, Rahane stays back and pushes it towards gully.
Runs for India and Rahane on Day 3! A shortish ball around middle, Rahane tucks it towards fine leg. Cummins from deep square leg runs to his right and makes a fine stop to save a couple of runs.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off for nothing.
A nasty bumper from Cummins to begin! He runs in and bangs it short. It is right at the body. Jadeja does really well to duck under it. Paine collects well over his head.
A length ball around off, Jadeja comes on the front foot and pushes it towards mid off.
Angled in and around off, pushed towards point.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms.
A short ball but this is outside off. Jadeja has no issues sitting under it.
A maiden to begin from Cummins. Good length and around off, Jadeja defends it out from the crease.
Fuller and around off, nicely pushed but straight to mid off.
On the pads, Rahane flicks it down to deep square leg for a run.
First run for Jadeja in the morning. A length ball around off, Jadeja looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket. They cross for a single.
On a length around off and middle, blocked.
Full and outside off, Rahane drives it on the up and through the covers. Returns for three before the fielder can chase it down. Fine shot.
A bumper to Jadeja. He negotiates well by ducking under it.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked down to deep square leg for one.
Length ball angled in, Jadeja looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the pad.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.

FOUR! Nicely done! A length ball just around off, Jadeja waits for it to get close and then looks to defend. The ball takes a thickish outside edge and goes to the left of gully. It races away to the third man fence.
A single now as he flicks this fullish ball on middle to fine leg.
Fuller and around off, Jadeja drives it well but finds the cover fielder.
Driven firmly again. This time it is to the right side of the cover fielder who makes a diving stop but Jadeja gets a single.
Length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Shortish and around off, kept out off the back foot.
A solid front foot push to mid off from Rahane now.
This time Rahane pushes it to mid off and calls for a quick single.
Length ball just outside off, poked towards point. Says no for the run.
Angled in from outside off, Rahane looks to defend but is hit high on the pad.
Landed around off, pushed towards Gully.
Fullish this time and it is just outside off, Rahane defends it towards covers.
And finally a bumper for Rahane from Cummins. Rahane went after it and pulled it well but the square leg fielder dived to his right to make a stop.
Play and a miss! Another short ball outside off, Rahane looks to cut but misses. Tried to actually play an upper cut but it was too close for that shot.
Flatter and around off to begin, Jadeja keeps it out off his back foot.
Flat and around off, Jadeja stays back to block.
This time he clips it to the right side of the square leg fielder for one.
Shortish and just outside off, punched towards the cover fielder.
On off, Rahane is solid in the defense on the front foot.
Full and on the pads, worked towards short fine leg for nothing. 1 run from Lyon's first over in the morning.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards covers.
Down the leg side. Left alone.
Short and on middle, Jadeja sits under it.
And another short ball but Jadeja has no problems dealing with it as he ducks.
Works this fuller ball on the pads to fine leg and moves to 49.
Length ball around off, solidly defended towards the cover fielder.
Flat and wide outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on the pads, worked towards short fine leg for nothing.
Shortish and just around off, Jadeja forces it towards point and thinks for a run but is sent back.
Tossed up and around off, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! RUN OUT! Oh, dear! Rahane is short and he has to go. Australia get the big wicket. He just batted and batted and batted but now he falls trying to sneak a single to help his partner get to his half ton. But Jadeja will be stranded on 49 for now and Rahane goes after playing a brilliant knock. A flatter ball around off, Jadeja pokes it towards point and calls for a risky run. Skipper Rahane responds. Labuschagne quickly gets to the ball and fires the throw at the keeper's end. Paine collects and takes the bails off. The third umpire has been called for. Replays roll in and it shows Rahane is short, short by a few inches only but he has to go. Such a sad end to a fantastic knock for the skipper. He was involved in a run out in the first game with Kohli and now as a skipper, he gets dismissed that way. A classy knock from him and a class act as he walks back. He pats Jadeja and probably asks him to carry on! Terrific innings and terrific gesture. Standing ovation from the crowd for the skipper as he walks off.
Tossed up and turning in, Ashwin works it towards fine leg. End of a successful over for Australia.

FIFTY FOR JADEJA! The Jadeja sword is out now and there goes the celebration. What an amazing art with the sword and even better with the willow in his hand. Such a valuable innings it has been from him. Came out in the middle, was welcomed with a few nasty bumpers but showed grit and determination and supported his skipper superbly. Ran him out just a while ago trying to get to the milestone but this time he flicks it down to fine leg for a single. The lead gets to 100 now. Time for him to get into the T20 mode?
A fuller ball around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
On the pads, Ashwin flicks it down to fine leg for a single to open his account.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Length and around off, pushed towards cover.
Bumper on the body, Jadeja is late in getting down. He gets hit on the body as the ball lobs to the keeper.
Tossed up outside off, pushed towards vovers for a single.
Tosses up on middle, Jadeja blocks this out.
Flatter around middle, defended back.
A tossed up ball just around off, defends it towards slip.
Short and wide, punched towards covers.
Flatter around middle, pushes on the on side for a single.
Shortish around middle, Jadeja pushes it towards point.
Short again on the body, Jadeja lets it be.
Shortish length on middle, poked towards point.
Short of a length outside off, Jadeja just lets it go.
Short of length around middle, pushed straight to covers.
Good ball to end the over! A shortish length just outside off, Jadeja thinks of playing at it but gets beaten.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Shortish and on middle, tucked towards square leg for one.
Tossed up and outside off, turns away as Jadeja pokes it towards point.
Short now, worked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Hammered! Another short ball, this time Jadeja rocks back and nails the pull down to the deep mid-wicket fence. Superb stroke and it brings up 300 for India.
On off, Jadeja stays back to keep it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on middle, worked to fine leg for one.
Good running! A length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja clips it to the left of the deep square leg fielder for a brace.
Outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Back of a length and outside off, Jadeja leaves again.

A snorter of a delivery! A sharp bumper and Jadeja had no clue how to deal with it. Starc was appealing and he thought there was some bat or maybe gloves. The Aussie skipper has a word with him but they do not go for the review. A well-aimed bumper, Jadeja hops and tries to fend it off but it gets big on him and goes to the keeper. An appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire.
Flat and on middle and leg, worked towards square leg.
Flatter around leg, defended on the on side.
Flatter around middle, Ashwin bunts this down.
Outside off this time, played towards covers.
Short of a length around middle, blocked on the backfoot.
Flatter around middle, Ashwin just plays it back to the bowler. Maiden to start after drinks.
Another sharp bumper from Starc. It is just outside off, Jadeja hops and tries to fend it off but misses.
Jadeja looks to go for it this time but he makes no connection.
Outside off on a length, pushed to point.
Play and a miss again! Starc has got is tail up. Lovely short ball that moves away a touch to beat the poke of Jadeja who is hoping around.

OUT! CAUGHT! The short ball plan works and Jadeja falls prey to it. He was probably frustrated off the short stuff and tried to take on the bowler. Starc banged it in again. Jadeja pulled it hard but he found Cummins at deep mid-wicket. A good sliding take from him as this one was hit flat. Replays showed that he juggled and held onto it on the second attempt. Starc is elated. End of a fine knock from Jadeja. India's lead is 111 right now.
A sharp bumper to Yadav now! Nasty stuff from Starc here. He tried to get away but gets hit on the body.
Flatter around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up and outside off, kept out.
Floated around off, defended on the off side.
Flatter ball on middle, Ashwin comes down and hits it straight to covers.

Dropped! Labuschagne fails to hold onto another one. Flat and on middle and leg, Ashwin looks to pull but gets it off the inside edge. It goes to leg gully where Labuschagne gets both hands but fails to hold on.
Flatter around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Ouch! Ashwin gets a blow on the body now! And he calls for the physio straightaway. A short of a length ball airmed at the body, Ashwin looks to pull but gets hit on the chest.
The response from Starc is another bumper! And Ashwin once again goes for the pull. Hits it down to deep square leg for one.
Another short ball, this time to Umesh. He wanted a piece of it too but at the last second bailed out from going for the pull.
Works this one down to deep square leg and opens his account.
Length and outside off, pushed towards point for one.
Another short ball. Yadav is late in getting down. This time he gets one on his shoulder. Rubs the area but doesn't show any sort of pain.
Flatter around middle, worked on the on side for a run.
FOUR! The broom comes out now. Flatter ball around middle, Yadav sweeps it well wide of the man at deep square leg. No chance for him to cut it off.
Shorter this time turning in, Yadav plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter outside off, defended towards covers.
He now winds up for the massive slow but mistimes it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
Full and wide outside off, Yadav strokes it through covers for a run. Yadav wanted the second but Ashwin sends him back.
Good length and around off, defended off the back foot.
Pushes this one wide of the gully fielder and takes one.
Another short one, Yadav looks to pull but misses.
And again! This time Umesh decides to duck under it.

An appeal for LBW but turned down! Starc changes plan and bowls a length ball. Yadav looks to hammer it down the ground but ends up getting an inside edge. An appeal from Starc but nothing from the umpire.
Turned down leg after pitching, Ashwin nudges it to short fine leg.
Full and wide outside off, Ashwin strokes it through the covers and takes two. He will feel a lot comfortable playing the spinner.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
Tossed up and on middle, easily negotiated by Ashwin.
Full and on middle and leg, flicked down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and around off and middle, turned towards the forward short leg fielder.
Length ball around off, Ashwin blocks this out.
Shorter this time outside off, Ashwin lets it go.
A length ball just outside off, pushed towards point for a run.
Short ball around middle and leg, Yadav ducks under it.
Shortish around middle, Yadav tried to pull but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Shortish around middle,, tucked it towards fine leg for a single.
Flatter around middle, Yadav tucks it on the leg side and takes a run.
On middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Flatter around middle, defended towards short leg.
Flat around off, Ashwin drives this one towards covers and takes a run.
Floated around middle, Yadav comes forward and defends.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lyon strikes and Yadav has to go. A tossed up ball outside off, the ball turns in. Yadav comes on the front foot and looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to the slip fielder. Smith there makes no mistake. Just too good for the tail-ender.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Ashwin lets it be.
Length ball around off, played towards gully.
Driven solidly but straight to the cover fielder.

OUT! CAUGHT! Hazlewood gets one now. His first in the game. A length ball outside off, Ashwin looks to drive but ends up getting it off the outer half. It goes just over Lyon who is at point. He makes no mistake and takes the catch easily. India lead by 130 runs.
Play and a miss! A length ball just around off, Siraj pokes at it away from his body to get beaten.
A bumper but it goes well over. Wided by the umpire.
Length ball around off, Siraj looks to drive but gets an inside edge on the pad. The ball goes to point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tossed up and around off and middle, Bumrah gets down and looks to play the slog sweep. He fails to connect it well and hits it high in the air. The deep square leg fielder, Head, runs to his left and takes the catch easily. India lead by 131 runs. With this wicket, it is Lunch on Day 3.

Appeal straightaway! A loud one from India but not out says the umpire. A length ball around the pads, Wade looks to work it out on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. They all go up in appeal but nothing from the umpire. No review from India and a good call because replay shows it was pitched outside leg.
A length ball, this one is pitched around off, it keeps going away as Wade lets it be.
Wide outside off, left alone again by Wade.
Fuller and around off, it comes back in, Wade does well to keep it out.
In the channel outside off, Wade offers no shot to it.
A maiden to start from Bumrah. This one is around off on a length, Wade comes on the front foot to defend. Top first over from Bumrah.
Length ball around off, kept out.
Full but down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Good leave! This one pitches around off and moves a touch as Burns shoulders arms. It goes just over the stumps.

Quick single and Burns is off the pair. A direct hit though would've been close. Fuller and around middle, Burns works it towards mid-wicket and goes for a run. Ashwin has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses as Burns dives to make his crease.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point.
Back of a length and around middle, Wade is on his toes to block. 1 from Umesh's first.

NOT OUT! Burns survives. The umpire's call saves Burns here. A terrific delivery from Bumrah. He runs in and bowls a perfect yorker. Burns looks to flick but he falls over as he tries to play across the line. He misses and the Indians appeal but the umpire turns it down. Rahane goes for the review after having a word with the bowler and other close-in fielders. Replays show that it has hit the shoes. But Ball Tracker confirms it to be umpire's call on hitting the wickets. A good review from India.
Good length in the channel outside off, left alone by Burns.
Fuller length just outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
A length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
NIce drive! A fuller ball outside off, Burns drives this one through the covers and take three before the fielder returns the ball back.
A fuller length around off, defended towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time Burns has to go. A superb delivery from Yadav. This one pitches just around off and then goes away just a hint. Burns has to play at it. And he does that but only ends up getting a nick behind. Pant makes no mistake and the Indians celebrate. However, Burns gets to his partner at the other end and decides to challenge the onfield call, at the very last moment. Time for the replays. And only one is all we need. The Hot Spot detects a faint outside edge. Another failure for Burns and this time he takes a review along with him. Poor from the Aussie opener. An unplayable ball from Umesh though that would've got best of the batsmen out.
Fuller ball sliding down, Marnus flicks this one towards fine leg for a single and gets off the mark.
Length ball around middle, defended towards mid-wicket.
Good length around off, Wade blocks it out.
Shortish around off, dabs it on the off side.
Shortish around off, pushes it on the off side and takes a quick run. A successful over from Yadav.
Length around off, pushes it towards covers and takes a run.
Good length and around off Labuschagne defends it out.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid on.
Fuller and around off, Labuschagne taps it on the off side and gets to the other end.
Banged in on middle, goes well over Wade who ducks. Good from Pant behind the sticks.
A leave to end! This one is angled in from outside off but Wade is sure about his off pole as he shoulders arms.
Good leave! But this wasn't too far away from the off pole. A shortish and outside off, comes back in a touch as Labuschagne lets it be. Goes just past the off pole but it was over it.
Another quick run! Full and around off, Labuschagne pushes it towards cover and takes a run.
Now Wade pokes one towards the off side for a quick single. Good from Australia.
Leading edge! A fullish ball around middle and leg, it pitches and then straightens a touch. Labuschagne looks to flick but gets a leading edge. Rahane at gully dives to his right to make a stop.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Close! A good leave though. This is good from Umesh too. He continies to bowl it just around off on a length. Marnus though is covering his sticks as he shoulders arms.
Another quick single. Fuller and around off, Wade pushes it gently towards cover for a quick run.
A bumper but it goes well over Labuschagne.
Fuller and around off, worked towards square leg.
Angled in from around off, Labuschagne tucks it wide of the fine leg fielder for one.
Third single in the over. A fuller one outside off, Wade pushes it towards cover and goes for a run as Siraj fumbles.
Around off on a length, defended off the front foot.
On a length outside off, left alone by Wade.
Shortish around middle, Wade blocks this out.

Bumper around middle and leg, Wade ducks under it. Umesh is limping and he is looking in some pain here. Yes. He is going off. Not a great sign for the Indians. Let's hope there is nothing serious. The Indians will surely want that because he was looking really good.Siraj will continue the over.
Siraj starts with a fuller ball outside off, Wade lets it go.
Good length around off, dabbed it towards point.
Length outside off, Wade plays it towards point.
FOUR! Nicely driven down the ground by Labuschagne as it was fuller ball around off. The mid on fielder had no chance to stop that one.
A length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Length around middle, flicked towards square leg for a run.
A fuller length on middle, Wade defends it straight back.
Fuller length around off, played towards mid-wicket.
Shortish this time around middle, Wade blocks this out on the off side.
Lovely drive to welcome Ashwin from Labuschagne. Ashwin tosses it full and bowls it wide outside off, it is driven through covers for a brace.
A single now as this quicker one is nudged down to deep square leg. This one pitched around off and spun back in.
Tosses this one to the left-hander now and Wade defends it off the front foot.
Another loopy ball around off, kept out.
Tossed up and around off, Wade blocks it out.
Fuller and on the pads, nudged towards short fine leg.
Length ball around off, watchfully defended by Labuschagne.
Shortish and just outside off, poked towards the gully fielder.
In the channel outside off, a leave from Labuschagne.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Length and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Single to end as the last ball is flicked down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Fullish around off, driven straight to covers.
Tossed up around off nudges towards square leg.
Slightly short around off, driven to the left of covers and they take a run. Siraj though midfields at covers and concedes another one.
Three now! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne cuts it to the left of Siraj who gives it a chase. A single saved near the ropes.
On middle, blocked out by Wade.
Full and on middle and leg, Wade negotiates it easily.
Length ball around off, blocked solidly.
A fuller length ball around off, Marnus plays it on the leg side.
Fuller around middle, Marnus flicks it towards square leg but can't beat him.
Short of a length around middle, turned away towards fine leg for a single.
A fuller length outside off angling across, left alone by Wade.
Length ball angling across, Wade lets it be.
Tossed up and around middle, worked towards short fine leg.
Full and on middle and leg, Labuschagne looks to defend but gets an inside edge that goes past the keeper towards fine leg. They take two.
Loopy ball around off, blocked.
Short and wide outside off, punched through covers. Three taken before the fielder can chase it down.
On off, Wade keeps it out.
Tossed up and outside off, Wade pushes it towards point.
Length around middle, flicked straight to square leg.
Fuller this time around off, Marnus drives it towards imd off.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets, AGAIN! Luck with Labuschagne here. A length ball that is pitched outside off, it comes back in sharply and hits the pad as he fails to connect. It looked to be hitting him high on the pads but Rahane takes the review. Replays show everything is perfect but it is just clipping the stumps. So, Marnus survives. A good review from India though as it could've gone either way.
Short ball outside off, Marnus pulls this uppishly but just falls wide of the square leg fielder and they take a single. Labuschagne is living dangerously here.
Shortish around off, Wade pushes it towards point and runs but is sent back by his partner. A risk is involved when the fielder ther is Jadeja.
Fuller ball on the stumps, Wade blocks this out.
Loopy ball around off, driven through the covers and they take three before the fielder returns it back.
Fuller around off, defended straight towards the cover fielder.
Flatter around middle, swept towards fine leg for a single.
Tossed up around leg, tucks it towards leg gully.
Fuller ball on middle, tucks it on the leg side.
Tossed up around middle, nudged towards short fine leg.
Good length and around off, pushed towards point.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Shortish and just outside off, Wade looks to punch but mistimes it.
Full and outside off, a mistimed drive towards cover this time.
FOUR! This should settle the nerves for Wade. Short and wide outside off, Wade crunches it through backward of point and finds the fence.
Just outside off on a length, poked towards Rahane at gully.
Flatter and on middle, tucked on the leg side for nothing.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up and around off, kept out.
Flat and around off, blocked by Marnus.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ashwin strikes and provides the much-needed breakthrough to the Indians. Lovely loopy ball around off and middle from him this time. It pitches and then turns in to Marnus. Labuschagne looks to defend coming forward but it takes the outside edge and goes straight to Rahane at first slip. The Indian skipper takes the catch easily. Good, little innings from him but Australia needed him to carry on.
Tossed up and on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket. End of a successful over from Ashwin.

NOT OUT! Pitching outside leg. A poor review from India this time. A length ball pitched down the leg side. It angles across the left-hander. Wade fails to put bat on ball and is hit on the pad. They appeal but not out says the umpire. That looked to pitching outside leg but Siraj is absolutely sure that he has got his man. Rahane goes with the bowler. And well, replays show it to be a poor call as it has pitched way outside leg. Poor, poor review.
Length ball around middle, defended by Wade.
Shortish outside off, poked towards point.
Fuller ball on middle, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
Length around middle, Wade taps this one on the off side.
Shortish around middle, Wade punches this one wide of mid-wicket and takes a couple.
Tossed up and just outside off, turns in, Smith defends.
On middle, kept out.
Flat and around off, Smith comes on the front foot to block.
Flatter and around off, Smith stays back to block this time.
On the pads, Smith flicks it to deep mid-wicket and opens his account.

Appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire and nothing either from the bowler. A tossed up ball on middle and leg, Wade goes for the sweep but gets it off the inside edge towards short fine leg. They take a run.
50 up for Australia as they run 4. A fullish length on middle, Wade flicks this at the gap through mid-wicket and runs four as Gill does well to chase it down.
Length ball around off, left alone.
Similar ball outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Short of a length outside off, punched nicely towards deep point for a single.
Fuller ball around off, angling in, Smith nudges it towards leg gully.
Length ball around off, Smith blocks this out.
Tossed up on the stumps, defended straight back.
Tossed up outside off, Wade brings the sweep shot and hits it towards fine leg for one
Tossed up and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Wade lets it be.
Another one wide outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
On middle, Wade keeps it out.
Full and around off, Smith uses his wrists and flicks it between square leg and leg gully for three. Nice work.
Length ball around off, blocked off the front foot.
Outside off, going further away. Wade lets it be.
Length ball around off, Wade defends it towards point.
Length ball angling across, left alone by Wade.
Fuller ball around off, driven towards mid off.
Tossed up around off, Smith comes down the track but gets an inside edge on his pads.
Floated around off, defended straight by Smith.
Shortish and outside off, punched towards cover for one.
Shortish and just outside off, punched towards cover.
Quick single as Wade drives it wide of the man at mid off.
Quicker one around off, turned on the leg side.
Length ball around middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball on middle, Wade drives this down the ground and they take a couple before Siraj who chases the ball from mid off returns the ball back.
Shortish around middle, Wade blocks this towards mid on.
Short ball on middle and leg, Wade comfortably ducks under it.
Length ball around off, Wade defends it back to the bowler.
Shortish around off, punched straight to the fielder at covers.
Flatter and around off, pushed toards mid on.
On middle, Smith comes forward and bunts it on the leg side.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up and outside off, Smith goes for the slog sweep. Doesn't connect it well and it goes to square leg.
Tossed up and just outside off, Smith stays back to block.

Nearly a wicket! Superb over from Ashwin. He set Smith up nicely. He got him out similarly in the first innings. And, almost got him here. Pitches it around off and middle and then it turns in with some extra bounce. Smith looks to work it on the leg side but gets it off the inside edge. It though doesn't carry to Pujara this time.
Bumper down the leg side. Wade ducks.
Another short one. Easily evaded by Wade.
Three in a row! Bumrah wants to keep Wade on strike! India want another one from Ashwin to to Smith.
FOUR! Lovely drive! A fuller ball on the stumps, Wade drives this past mid on to get a boundary here.
In the channel outside off, left alone this time.
Bumper on middle, Wade sits again.
Smith takes a single on the first ball. Full and around middle, Smith pushes it to wide of the man at mid on for a run.
Tossed up and outside off, Wade is early in his defense as he ends up hitting it uppishly wide of the cover fielder.
Tossed up and around off, Wade keeps it out.

Was there some bat? Maybe not. Lovely from Ashwin. Flatter and around the pads, Wade goes back and looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball lobs towards forward short leg. The fielder lunges forward to take the catch but it drops short. Wasn't any bat anyway.
Tosses it up full and wide, turns away, Wade lets it be.
Another one tossed up outside off, Wade covers his stumps and allows it to go to the keeper. With that, it is TEA ON DAY 3.
Run straightaway for Smith! A length ball around off, Smith pushes it towards mid on and calls for a run.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Another one just outside off, Wade covers his stumps and lets it go to Pant.
Pitches this up and bowls it just around off, Wade defends it out.
Length ball around off and middle, pushed to mid on.
Very full and on middle, flicked towards mid on for nothing.
And Smith nudges one towards mid-wicket to get to the other end.

What happened there? A tossed up ball just around off, it pitches and bounces over the stumps to beat the bat. Pant is beaten too. The ball lobs off the shoulder of Pant and goes behind. Rahane goes back to field.
On middle and leg, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up and around middle, Wade is on the front foot to block.
Another solid defense to end the over.
Shortish and around off, blocked off the back foot.
Good length and just around off, pushed on the off side.
Fuller and around off, blocked towards mid on by Smith.
Good length and around off, it is angled in. Smith flicks but square leg dives to his right to stop.
A bouncer now. Smith ducks under it.
A maiden from Bumrah as the last ball is worked towards mid-wicket. Tight from Bumrah.
Fuller and around middle and leg, Wade blocks.
Slower through the air and around off, blocked from the crease.
Tosses this up but Wade is happy to defend again.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
On off, blocked towards silly point.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Tossed up and outside off, Wade throws his bat at the drive and makes a good connection. Agarwal at mid off fails to get to his right and stop the ball cleanly. It races down to the fence at long off.
Edgy! Fuller and around off, Smith looks to defend but it goes to gully off the outside edge. Played with soft hands though.

OUT! TIMBER! Smith is not sure what happened but the bails are disloged! Smith has been bowled around his legs. He is not sure and is hanging around. A length ball around middle and leg, Smith shuffles across the off side, like he always does and tries to work this one on the leg side but he misses. That doesn't happen often but it has happened here. And the ball goes on to dislodge the bail from the leg and middle pole. Smith is not sure what happened as Bumrah and the Indians celebrate. Smith hangs around and the onfield umpire asks the help from the TV umpire. And one replay is enough. Smith has to go. It is yet another failure for him in this series. A massive, massive moment in the game.

Just over! What a welcome for Head! A snortner of a delivery first up. This is just around off, Head hops and tries to fend it off but it takes the gloves and goes over Rahane at gully. A single for Head.
Length ball around off, Head keeps it out.
A bouncer! Wade sits under it.
A single to end the successful over for India. Good length and around off, poked towards backward point for one. Bumrah has overstepped. So, he needs to re-bowl this one again.
The extra ball costs two. Shortish and around off, Wade tucks it through square leg for a couple. End of a successful over from Bumrah.
Fulller and around off, Wade blocks off his front foot.
Tossed up and outside off, Wade sweeps it nicely wide of the man at fine leg. Siraj though runs to his right, puts in a dive and stops two.
Tossed up and outside off, blocked.
Short and wide outside off, Wade cuts it hard but finds point.
Tossed up this time, Wade stays back to block.
Flatter and around middle and leg, Wade does well to block.
Fuller and around middle, Head flicks it towards mid-wicket. Thakur misfields and they run three.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
Length ball around off, defended towards the bowler.
Nasty bumper and Wade gets the blow on his helmet. A bumper and Wade takes his eyes off the ball as he tries to duck away from it. He calls for a new helmet straightaway.
Short ball again as Wade this time ducks under it.
Good testing over this by Bumrah. Another Short ball, Wade ducks again.
Tossed up and outside off, Head lets it be.
Full and around off, kept out.
Flatter up and around off, Head pushes it towards mid off.
Slower through the air and around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a brace.
Tossed up and around middle, turned on the leg side.
Short and wide, Head cuts but hits the silly point fielder.
Good length and around off, Wade tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Full and on middle and leg, Head flicks but finds leg gully. It wasn't too far from the fielder.
Shortish and around off, Head gets on his toes to defend.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Length and on the pads, Head flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Wow! That was a nasty bumper. Head does well to duck as it went past his ear. Sensational stuff.
A single on his first ball as Wade pushes it through mid off for one.
Tossed up and outside off, Head drives it through the cover region for a couple.
Short and wide outside off, Head cuts but finds the point fielder.
Flatter and around off, turning in, Head hits it hard on the leg side but Gill comes in the middle and gets a blow on his shoulder.
Tossed up and outside off, driven towards mid off.
Tossed up and outside off, kept out.
Flatter and around off, pushed towards point.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards the off side.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket for one.
Flat and on off, played back to Ashwin by Head.
On the pads, Head flicks but finds square leg.
Lovely delivery to end the over. Quicker and just outside off, Head looks to cut but he is cramped for room. Ends up missing it and Pant behind fails to hold on. Was there any bat? No.
Tossed up outside off, Wade sweeps it wide of the man at fine leg for a couple.
On off, Wade knocks it on the off side and gets to the other end.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed to the left of the bowler.
Flatter and around off, Head stays back to defend.
Loopy ball on middle, Head works it towards mid-wicket.
A single on the last ball as it is worked towards square leg.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on the pads, Head flicks but finds square leg.
Loopy ball around off, a solid front foot defense.
Tossed up on middle, Head blocks again.
Shortish and around off, this time it is punched to the right of the mid off fielder. They take a quick run.
Ripper to end! This one pitches just around off and Wade comes on the front foot to defend but it spins away and whizzes past the outside edge. Pant does well to collect.
Full and just outside off, poked towards point by Head.
Shortish and around off, turns in as Head punches but finds Ashwin at cover-point who makes a diving stop to his left.
On off, blocked off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle and leg, turned on the leg side.
Short and wide outside off, Head looks to cut but misses. Some excitement from the Indians but nothing from the umpire.
Floated on middle and leg, worked towards mid on.
Tossed up and around off, defended.
Loopy around off, Wade is on the front foot to block again.
On middle, kept out by Wade.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
Loopy ball just around off, it turns away as Wade forces it on the off side.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
On middle, flicked towards fine leg for a couple. Siraj chases the ball and keeps it to two.
Flatter on middle, tucked towards square leg for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Shortish and on middle, worked towards the man at mid-wicket.
Good stop from Ashwin. Short and wide outside off, Wade cuts but Ashwin dives to his left and stops.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and Wade departs. That looked plumb and Wade knew it but he took the review sensing the importance of this wicket. A quicker one from Jadeja, it is the slider from him. Wade looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get rapped on the pad. The Indians appeal and the finger goes up. Wade is distraught as he knows he is a goner but he takes the review. The technology won't help him as it shows three reds on the Ball Tracker. He has to go. Waste of a review from him. A good, fighting knock from Wade though.
Tossed up and around middle, blocked by Head off the front foot.
Full ball on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
On off, driven to mid off for nothing.
Tossed up and outisde off, Head drives but finds short cover.
Loopy and around off, Head keeps it out off his front foot.
Flat and just outside off, poked towards point.
Tossed up around off, defended back.
Flatter around off, fended straight back.
On middle and off, punched towards covers.
On middle, defends straight back.
Quicker one on the pads, worked on the leg side.
On middle, played back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj strikes on the first ball of his new spell. What an amazing bowling change from Rahane. Half the Aussie side are back in the hut. Siraj is fired up and why not. Australia in all sorts of trouble. A good length ball outside off, Head throws his bat at it as he looks to cut but ends up getting a thick outside edge. It goes straight to Mayank at second slip who takes it easily. Head falls cheaply again.
Length ball around off, blocked out.
Another length ball around off, Paine is solid in defense.
Shortish and on middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Landed around off on a length, kept out.
Full and on middle, clipped through mid-wicket and Paine is off the mark. Single and a wicket from the over.
Tossed up and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Floated on off, driven towards covers this time.
On middle, Paine comes on the front foot and pushes it towards mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Paine has to go as RTS spots an edge. Paine is not pleased. He just cannot believe it. A tossed up delivery just outside off, it turns away and bounces extra as Paine looks to cut but misses. Pant collects and appeals along with the bowler. Not out says the umpire but Rahane goes for the review straightaway. The Hot Spot rolls in. Nothing on it. RTS detects the bat. The onfield call has to be changed. OUT it is and Paine departs. What a review from Rahane. India all over Australia at the moment.
On middle, clipped to fine leg for a brace by Cummins to open his account.
Full and around off, defened back to the bowler. Another successful over from Jadeja.
Length ball around off, defended straight.
Length on middle, played it down t on the on side.
A length ball on middle, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
Length on middle, played with a straight bat.
Bumper now on middle and leg, Green ducks under it.
Length on middle, punched down the ground, the bowler gets a hand and diverts it towards mid off to give away the run.
Around off, pushed towards mid off.
Flatter around off, driven towards covers and takes a quick run does Green. Called no ball as Jadeja has overstepped.
Flatter around off, defended on the off side.
Shortish and around off, Pat stays back to defend.
Loopy and around off, Cummins pushes it towards cover.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.

Huge appeal for LBW but turned down. That looked to be going down leg but Siraj was once again confident. But this time Rahane wasn't listening to him. Length ball angled in from outside off, Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses. They appeal but turned down. Replays show it to be missing leg by some distance.
Fuller length outside off, left alone.
Length on middle, tucked on the leg side for a run.
Cummins defends it on the back foot.
Length ball around middle, flicked towards backward square leg.
Similar ball, tucked away towards backward square leg.
Flatter around off, defends it on the off side.
Fuller ball defended of the front foot.
A tossed up ball played back to the bowler.
Flatter and around off, Green goes back to block.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed back to Jadeja.
Quicker one around middle, defened from within the crease. A maiden.
Sharp bouncer! It is just outside off, Green sways away.
Good length and around off, Cummins pushes it towards point.
Fuller and around off, Cummins comes on the front foot to defend.
Another good bumper! Cummins sits under it.
Around off on a length, solid block from Pat.
Shot! Full and outside off, Cummins nails the drive through the covers. Ashwin chases it down and they take three.
Floated around off, blocked by Pat.
Full and on middle, worked towards square leg for one.
Quicker and around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up and around off, Green pushes it towards mid off and takes a quick single.
Floated outside off, driven well by Cummins but straight to the cover fielder.
Tossed up and around off, blocked out.
A length ball around off to begin, Green blocks.
Bouncer on middle, Green sits under it.
Around off on a length, Green keeps it out.
Length around off, dabs it towards point.
Fuller this time, played softly towards covers.
Bouncer to finish the over, Green ducks under it.
FOUR! Tossed up around off, Cummins goes over the top of mid off and gets a boundary. Some aggression now from Cummins.
Shorter this time, punched to the left of cover for a single.
FOUR! Hammered! A short ball on middle, Green rocks back and powers it over mid-wicket. One bounce and into the gence.
Flatter and around off, Green goes back to block.
Shortish and around off, forced towards the cover fielder.
Jadeja slows this up and bowl it full around off, Green stays back to defend.
Length ball around middle, bunts it down towards mid on.
Fuller this time around off, played straight back to the bowler.
Good length around off, defended solidly.
Length around off, blocked by Cummins.
Bumper around off, Cummins sits under it.
Attempted slower yorker ends up being a full toss. Cummins does well to block. Good variation by Bumrah to end the over.
Floated around off, blocked.
Loopy ball around off and middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Flatter and outside off, forced wide of the man at gully for one.
Around off on a shortish length. Cummins blocks.
Shortish again, kept out.
Floated full and on middle, Cummins comes forward and blocks.
A bouncer around off, Green ducks under it.
And again but this one is down the leg side. Green has no issues dealing with it.
Shortish and around middle, Green gets on top of the bounce to block. Called no ball.
Lovely yorker! Green somehow manages to get bat on ball.
Ouch! A bumper and Green is late in getting down. He gets hit on the arm. Doesn't show any sort of pain there.
Bouncer again, this time Green ducks.
Good length and around off, Green this time is solid in defense.
Tossed up on middle and off, dabs it towards point.
Floated around off, pushed back.
Beaten! Was there an edge there? A tossed up ball outside off, beats Cummins and Pant fails to collect it. Replays show there was a faint edge, so a chance put down by Pant.
Floated around off, blocked by Cummins.
Flatter and around middle, Cummins pushes it to mid on for one.
Looped up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Yorker on middle, Cummins does well to block it.
Short time but down the leg, Cummins ducks under it.
Shortish around leg, tucked away towards deep square for a single.
Short again on middle, Green this time ducks under it.
Lovely yorker from Bumrah. Green does well to block. Excellent from both bowler as well as the batter there.
Bouncer to end the over, but down the leg, easily evaded by Green.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for one.
Short again, this time Green punches it wide of the cover fielder for one.
Tossed up and around off, watchfully blocked.
Pushes this fuller one gently to the right side of Ashwin for a run.
Tossed up around off, turns in but Green is up for the task as he blocks.
Floated full on the pads, kept out but Green.
Bangs the first one short and it is aimed at the body. Cummins does well to get down.
Outside off on a length, Cummins drives but finds the cover fielder.
Around off on a length, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length and around off, Cummins defends it out solidly again.
Back of a length and around middle, Pat stays back to block.
A maiden from Siraj. A length ball around middle and leg, Cummins pushes it towards mid on.
Play and a miss! Darted outside off, Green looks to cut but misses.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Shortish and just outside off, played towards the off side.
Tossed up and outside off, forced towards cover region for one.
Fuller and around off, Cummins is on the front foot to defend.

Uppish but safe! Lovely from Ashwin. He tosses the last ball up and bowls it full on middle and leg, Cummins goes for the flick and does so uppishly towards mid-wicket. The ball though falls well short.
Full and wide outside off, left alone by Green.
Landed around off in a good length, a solid front foot block.
Beaten! Fuller and outside off, Green goes for the big booming drive through the off side but is beaten all ends up.
Short time time but way down the leg side. Green lets it go.
Shortish on the body, Green just tucks this one towards fine leg for a single.
Length just around off, Cummins pushes this one towards point and runs, but returns back as his partner says a loud no.
Floated full and on middle, Green comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! SHOT! Short and wide outside off, Green punches it past the man at mid off for a boundary. Australia take the lead. They are ahead by one.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller and around middle, Green works it towards deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Tossed up and around off and middle, turns in but Cummins blocks.
Slower through the air and around middle and leg, Cummins stays back to block. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 3.

Runs straightaway! A length ball around off from Bumrah to begin, Green pushes it to the right of the fielder at point and they go for a quick single. He has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses. The Aussies get one more in the form of overthrows as there is no one to back it up.
Down the leg side, Green looks to flick but misses.
Good length and around off, a solid front foot defense from Green.
Around off on a length, Green defends it out.
Solid again from Green. Another length ball around off from Bumrah. Green moves across to the off side and then blocks.
A single on the last ball. Another length ball around off, Green looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes towards square leg for a run.
Tossed up and just outside off, turning in, Green goes back and blocks.
Flatter and just outside off, Green stays back to defend.
Floated outside off, easily defended.
Fuller and around off, Green blocks again.
Slower through the air and a bit shortish in length. Green is on his back foot to block.
Tossed up and on middle, this time Green lunges ahead to defend. A maiden from Ashwin.
Fuller and around off, Cummins keeps it out.

Edged but short! Lovely from Bumrah. After bowling the first ball on the stumps, Bumrah bowls this one just outside off on a good length. Cummins pokes at it without moving his feet. An outside edge is induced but the ball doesn't carry to Pujara at first slip.
Good length and around middle, worked on the leg side.
Another length ball, tucked towards square leg.
Back of a length ball around off, Pat gets on top of the bounce to block.
A maiden from Bumrah now. This is once again shortish in length and around middle, Cummins blocks it out.
Full and around middle, pushed down to long on for one.
Flatter and around off, pushed towards point.
Quicker one on the pads, tucked on the leg side.
Shortish and around middle, kept out off the back foot.
Tossed up and around off, Cummins blocks. It looked like he wanted to go over the top for a moment but opted against it at the end. Ashwin gave the ball a lot of loop and slowed it down too.
Fuller and around middle, turned towards short fine leg for nothing by Cummins.
Fuller and around off, Green is solid in defense.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Landed on a length and on middle, worked down to fine leg for one.
Banged short this time, Cummins sits under it. First bouncer of the morning.
Wide outside off, Cummins shoulders arms.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
Floated on middle, kept out.
Tossed up and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up and around off, Green comes down the track and flicks but finds mid-wicket.
This time he comes down the track and pushes it down to long on for one.
Tossed up outside off, Pat looks to defend but the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes towards gully.
Turn and bounce there. This one pitches around off and then turns in and bounces extra. Cummins goes back and fends it off the inner half through leg gully for one.
Good length and around off, pushed towards point.
Fuller and wide outside off, driven to the left of the cover fielder for one.
Outside off on a good length, left alone.
Another one wide outside off, Green makes another leave.
Good leave! This one comes in with the angle from outside off as Green shoulders arms.
Good length and around off, kept out by Green. Decent first over from Siraj.
Tossed up and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Good running! Floated outside off, Cummins stays back and then guides it towards third man. They take two.
Floated on the pads, Cummins pads it away.
Loopy outside off, left alone.
Tossed up and around off, blocked off the front foot.

Huge appeal from Ashwin but turned down. Pant tells Ashwin that it won't hit the stumps. No review from the Indians. This is again tossed up and is bowled on middle and leg, Cummins pads it away again as Ashwin appeals but nothing from the umpire. Replay later rolled in and it showed it would've gone over the timbers and it would've missed it by some margin.
Length ball around off, blocked.
On a good length, defended solidly.
Fuller around off, driven to mid off.
Good length, blocked solidly.
Bouncer on middle, Green ducks under it. Someone may have told Siraj that Green was standing outside the crease.
Shortish around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
On off, defended.
Flat and around off, blocked.

NOT OUT! Missing leg and going over too. India lose a review. A quicker one around middle and leg, Cummins pads it away and the Indians appeal but not out says the umpire. Ashwin thinks he has got his man. Rahane thinks, thinks and just thinks. And then at the last moment, takes the review. Doesn't help India as the Ball Tracker shows it is missing the leg pole.
Floated around middle, tucked towards square leg for single.
Tossed up around middle, blocked.
Floated around off, Green comes down and defends.
Flatter around off, blocked by Pat.
Fuller this time, defended towards the bowler.
Flatter around off, turned towards mid-wicket.
Shortish and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Appeal for LBW, a loud one from Jadeja but the umpire is unmoved. This is the slider from Jadeja. It pitches on middle and leg and Cummins misses his flick to get hit on the pad.
Excellent stop at gully. Gill is the man. Shortish and just outside off, Cummins cuts but Gill dives to his left to save runs.
Shortish and around off, punched through covers for brace.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Green comes down the track and pushes it down to long off for one.
On middle, pushed wide of the leg gully fielder for a single.
Green once again uses his feet. This time he covers the spin and defends.
Loopy ball around off, a solid front foot defense. It was the carrom ball but Green read it well.
Flat and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, defended back to Jadeja again.
Floated around off, blocked.
Tossed up and around off, Cummins comes on the front foot to block.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Another leave as Jadeja bowls it wide outside off.
A quick single as Green pushes it to mid on. The single brings up 50-run stand between the two.
Loopy ball on the legs, Pat pads it away.
Looped ball and on middle, kept out.
Another loopy ball around middle, Cummins taps it onto the pitch.
Tossed up and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, Cummins is solid in defense again.
A fullish ball outside off to begin, Green lets it be.
Another fuller one outside off, shapes away further after going past the batter.
Appeal for LBW but nothing doing. A length ball around off, this one came back in after pitching. Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
Outside off, left alone.
Very full and around off, blocked towards mid on.
A solid defense this time from Green off the front foot. A maiden.
Flatter and around middle, kept out.
Short and wide, Cummins punches it wide but Siraj dives to his right at covers to keep it for a run. 150 is up for the Aussies and the lead is 19.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
FOUR! First boundary of the day. Short and wide outside off, Green slashes it through point for a boundary.
Flatter and around middle and leg, pushed to mid on.
Quick single! Floated around off, it is pushed towards mid off and they take a quick run.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Full and around middle, flicked wide of the man at mid-wicket for one.
Outside off on a good length. Left alone.

OUT! TAKEN! Bumrah with a snorter and Cummins has no answers to that. After bowling length deliveries outside off, this time Bumrah bends his back and bowls a short ball around middle and leg. Cummins is caught in an awkward position as he hops and tries to fend it off. All he does is lobs the ball off the gloves to Agarwal at second slip. A gritty knock from Cummins but that was an unplayable ball from Bumrah.

Another bumper! This time to the new man. Starc has no clue how to deal with it. Tries to duck but is late in doing so. The ball takes the top edge and goes to fine leg. The fielder there does well to stop the ball. They check with the third umpire and it is a good save. End of a superb over from Bumrah.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked.
Loopy ball around off, blocked out.
Outside off, left alone.
The quicker one on the pads, Starc looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Tossed up and outside off, Starc punches it well but hits it straight at the man at silly point.
Good length and around off, poked towards point.
Fullish and outside off, pushed to mid off.
Banged short to Green, this goes down the leg side as Green ducks.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around middle, Green flicks well but finds mid-wicket.
Bumrah goes for the yorker but Green flicks it nicely. It is wide of the man at fine leg. Before he can come around, they take three.
Short and outside off, pushed to mid on.
Flatter and outside off, played back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, poked towards mid off.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
A single and Green will keep the strike. Shortish and around off, played to long on for a run. Should've had got the long on fielder inside the ring.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and around off, kept out.
Fullish and just outside off, Green is solid in defense.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bumrah misses his line and bowls it on the pad. Green looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes to the fine leg fence past the diving keeper.
Fuller and around off, blocked.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Green slashes it through backward point and finds the fence. Good way to end the over.
Tossed up and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Loopy on middle, solid front foot block.
Tossed up and around middle, again kept out by Starc.
On off, kept out.
Two now and the lead goes to 40. Full and on middle, Starc flicks it through mid-wicket and scampers back for the second.
Full and way outside off, Green leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! Starc has done well there. A length ball around off, Green pushes it back to the bowler. Siraj in his followthrough gets his hands to it as the ball goes to hit the stumps. They appeal. The third umpire has been called for. Replays show Starc has got himself in.
Full ball on middle, Green does well to block it.

Close! A fuller ball outside off, Green drives it towards mid off and starts to run, but then sends Starc back, who just makes it at the non striker's end as the mid off fielder has a shy at the stumps.
Fuller around off, defended towards covers.
A dot on the last ball. So, Starc will be back on strike. Good from Siraj. He bends his back and bangs it short. Green ducks under it.
Full and around off, blocked back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, pushed to mid off this time.
On off, kept out.
Fuller and around middle, flicked down to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up and around off, watchfully blocked.
Flatter and just outside off, pushed to the right of the man at mid off. Now, Siraj will have a go at Starc in the next over.
Appeal but nothing from the umpire. Fuller and on middle and leg, Starc looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
KL Rahul, the substitute with a fine stop. Fuller and around off, Starc drills it towards mid on. Rahul runs to his left and dives to stop. Just a run. Saves 3.
Wide outside off, left alone.
FOUR! SHOT! FIne shot! Fuller and around middle, Green drills it to the right of the man at mid on. He gives it a chase but comes second.
Fuller and around off, kept out.

OUT! TAKEN! Green falls. The debutant has got the job done for India here. India one step closer to the win. A shortish ball around middle, Green looks to pull. However, it goes off the higher part of his bat and goes to Jadeja at mid-wicket. He seems to have lost it for a moment but does well to catch over his head. A fighting knock from Green comes to an end. Australia lead by 46 runs.
Flatter and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Slower through the air and on middle, defended.
On off, driven to long off for one.
Lyon is off the mark now. This is tossed up nicely. Lyon goes back and pokes it to gully for one.
Tossed up full and around middle, Starc blocks.
On the pads on a fullish length, Starc is blocking it again.
Fuller ball outside off, Lyon drives it towards covers.
Similar ball, similar shot from Lyon but straight to the fielder.
Fuller length on middle, flicked away towards mid on.
Short around middle, Lyon pulls this one towards fine leg for a single.
Short this time to Starc but outside off, Starc leaves it alone.
Almost gets him! A fuller length ball around off, Starc looks to play at it, but misses and the ball goes through to Pant.
Flat and around off, pushed back to Ashwin.
Fuller and around middle, Lyon tucks it towards short fine leg.
Tossed up outside off, Lyon goes for the drive but gets a thick outside edge that goes wide of the man at point. They take a run. The lead is now 50.
Beaten! Superb ball from Ashwin. This one pitches around leg and then goes away as Starc looks to defend but is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, kept out off the back foot this time.
A bumper around off, Lyon sways away from the line.
This one is on middle and leg, Lyon ducks under it.
Fuller and on the pads, Lyon looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes wide of the man at short fine leg and they take a leg bye.
Good length and around off, poked towards point.
Bumper just around off, Starc lets it go to Pant.
Full and on middle, flicked down to fine leg for a run.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Play and a miss! Flat and wide outside off, Starc looks to punch but misses.
Just short. Full and on middle, Starc flicks it uppishly. It is just short of the man at mid-wicket.
Misfield and two! Flat and around middle, Starc flicks it to the left of the mid-wicket fielder who misfields and allows two.
Tossed up and around off, Starc is on the front foot to block.

NOT OUT! Technology saves Starc. Flat ball around off, Starc looks to flick but misses. The ball hits his pad and goes to first slip. Rahane takes the catch and they appeal. The finger is raised. And Starc takes the DRS straightaway. Replays roll in. It shows that his bat has hit his shoes which is detected by the Hot Spot. The umpire checks the LBW call as well. Ball Tracker shows missing the stumps.
Shorter around middle, tucked towards leg gully.
Fuller ball on middle, driven to mid on.
Length on middle, Lyon looks to tuck but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj gets another one. Australia are 9 down. The effort ball from Siraj. He bangs it short and on middle and leg, Lyon goes for the pull but ends up getting a bit of gloves to the left of the keeper. Pant moves that way and takes the catch. They appeal and once again the finger has gone up.  Lyon knows he has hit it. He keeps walking. Wicket number 3 for Siraj. Australia leading by 54 runs.

FIVE RUNS! Needless from Siraj. A shortish ball around middle, Josh tucks it towards the leg side and goes for a quick single. Siraj quickly gets to the ball and has a needless shy at the non-striker's end. He misses and there is no one doing the back up and the ball races away to the long off fence.
Swing and a miss! Short ball on middle, Starc goes for the pull but makes no connection. End of a successful over from Siraj.
A bumper straightaway. Hazlewood fends it towards short fine leg for one.
Short ball on middle, Starc sits under it.
Yorker this time! Starc does well to flick it down to fine leg for a run.
Baged short but down the leg side. Josh ducks under.
Goes for the yorker but ends up bowling a full toss. Starc mistimes it towards short fine leg.
Length ball around off, Hazlewood looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg. They cross.
Short ball on middle, kept out.
Short on middle again, Hazlewood looks to play the upper cut but misses.
Follows the short ball with a length ball around off, beating Hazlewood's defence.
Almost! A shorter on middle, Hazlewood looks to fend, but misses and the ball goes to Pant.
A mixture of short and length ball here by Siraj. A length ball just around off, misses the edge.
Bouncer around off, Josh allows it to go to the keeper by dropping his hands.
Short on leg, tucks this one towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball on middle, defended on the back foot.
Beaten! Length ball outside off, angles away and beats the outside edge of Starc.
A bumper now! Josh sits under it.
Full and outside off, stroked through covers for a brace.
Good bouncer to end the over! Starc does well to get away from the firing line.
Length ball around middle, Starc looks to work it on the leg side but gets a leading edge towards gully.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, Starc lets it go.
Length ball angled in, Starc tucks it through square leg for a single.
A well-directed bumper. Hazlewood does well to move out of the way.
Slower fuller one around off, Hazlewood reads it well and pushes it towards cover.
Flatter and around middle, Starc tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Shortish and just outside off, pushed towards point.
On off, a solid front foot defense this time.
Short and on middle, Starc pulls it wide of the man at fine leg for a couple.
Tossed up outside off, turns way as Starc watches it go to the keeper.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Starc survives a calls that could've gone against him. Flighted ball on the pads, Starc looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get his on the pads. The Indians put in a loud appeal but it is turned down. Rahane goes for the review. Hot Spot and RTS confirm no bat. Ball Tracker shows it would just clip the leg pole. So, Starc stays to continue the battle. India keep their review.
Fuller and outside off, pushed to point.
A length ball around of, poked past gully towards third man for a single. 200 up for Australia now and they lead by 69 now.
Shorter around off, Starc sways away from it.
Short on middle, Starc ducks under it.
Outside off on a length, left alone.
Yorker on middle, Starc digs it out.

OUT! TIMBER! Ashwin with the success. A flat ball around middle and leg, Hazlewood thinks that it will spin away way too much as he shoulders arms. To his dismay, the ball clips the off pole and takes the bails along with it. Australia are bowled out for 200. India need 70 to level the series.
Starc is on the money straightaway. A shortish length ball around off, angles in as Agarwal fails to put bat on ball and is hit on high on the pad.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Play and a miss! Lovely ball from Starc. He makes this one to come back in from around off and cut Mayank in half.
Agarwal is up and running. A length ball around middle and leg, Agarwal tucks it towards deep square leg for one.
Chance but a tough one. A length ball around middle, Gill flicks. There is a forward short leg. Wade it is. The ball goes straight to him but he fails to hold on.
Gill is off the mark on the last ball of the over. A length ball around middle, Gill works it down to deep square leg to open his account.

FOUR! SHOT! Full and wide outside off, Gill strokes it through the covers for a boundary. Super shot from Gill. Tells you how confident this young man is. Classy shot against the no. 1 Test bowler in the world.
Taps the next one towards point and takes a run.
Length ball around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Nicely bowled! Pitches this one outside off and it comes back in sharply. Agarwal is caught on crease as he tries to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Another ripper! Sensational from Cummins. This one pitches just outside off and comes back in again as Agarwal pokes. Only to get beaten.
Works the last ball through backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off
FOUR! WOW! What a shot! Gill bags another boundary. Starc overpitches it around off, Gill meets it with straight bat and just punches the drive through mid off. It races away to the fence.
Good length and around off, watchfully blocked off the back foot.
Beaten! Flirts with one which is outside off to get beaten.
This time the line is way wide outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
Shortish and around off, Gill gets on top of the bounce and taps it on the off side.
In the channel outside off, Agarwal shoulders arms.
Another leave as Cummins continues to bowl in the channel on a good length.
Good length and just outside off, poked towards point off the front foot. Good, positive stride from him.
Outside off again, Agarwal lets it be.
Full and outside off, Mayank leans into the drive and strokes it through covers for a brace.
Around off on a length, Agarwal lets the ball to come close and then forces it towards gully.
Nicley pulled! A well-directed bumper but Gill does really well to play a controlled pull shot wide of the man at fine leg. A single.

OUT! TAKEN! Starc gets one. Poor from Agarwal. He fails in this short run chase. Hasn't been a great tour for him and it continues to be that way. It is just outside off on a length, it pitches and moves away. Agarwal looks to drive it on the up and ends up getting a nick behind. Paine accepts the chance easily.
Pujars is up and running with a brace. Starc targets the stumps and bowls it full on middle, Pujara flicks and bags two.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
Taps the next fuller one towards point and gets to the other end.
Short and wide outside off, punched to the man at point. End of a successful over from Starc.
